database_info.description: Complete EDOPro ID to Rush Duel card name mapping

160001000.name: Blue-Eyes White Dragon (Rush)
160001000.description: This legendary dragon is a powerful engine of destruction. Virtually invincible, very few have faced this awesome creature and lived to tell the tale.

160001001.name: Lizard Soldier (Rush)
160001001.description: A beast soldier derived from dragons, it is small for a Dragon Type. Moving very quickly, this monster is an excellent strategist.

160001002.name: Lesser Dragon (Rush)
160001002.description: A minor dragon incapable of breathing fire.

160001003.name: Ancient Turtle Protector
160001003.description: A respecter of tradition that reminisces about times long past. Those really were the good old days.

160001004.name: Binding Chain (Rush)
160001004.description: The mystic links of this chain can rob enemies of their power.

160001005.name: Tang the Noodle Ninja
160001005.description: A ninja who is proud of his chewy noodles and their unique texture. Those bound by his soup-infused noodles cannot escape.

160001006.name: Little D (Rush)
160001006.description: Yo, this tyrannosaurus tot's got a terrible temper.

160001007.name: Arma Knight (Rush)
160001007.description: An ammonite warrior that has protected the seas throughout history.

160001008.name: Petit Moth (Rush)
160001008.description: This small but deadly creature is better off avoided.

160001009.name: Skull Servant (Rush)
160001009.description: A skeletal ghost that isn't strong but can mean trouble in large numbers.

160001010.name: Silver Fang (Rush)
160001010.description: A snow wolf that's beautiful to the eye, but absolutely vicious in battle.

160001011.name: Feral Imp (Rush)
160001011.description: A playful little fiend that lurks in the dark, waiting to attack an unwary enemy.

160001012.name: Faith Bird (Rush)
160001012.description: This long-tailed bird blinds its enemies with mystical light.

160001013.name: LaMoon (Rush)
160001013.description: A sorcerer that draws its powers from the lunar landscape.

160001014.name: Machine Attacker (Rush)
160001014.description: This machine, created to lead charges into enemy territory, mows down enemies by rushing.

160001015.name: Crawling Dragon (Rush)
160001015.description: This weakened dragon can no longer fly, but is still a deadly force to be reckoned with.

160001016.name: Max Raider
160001016.description: An axe-wielding warrior. He has pushed himself to the limit in honing his body. The attacks from the two axes he brandishes are quite powerful.

160001017.name: Kuribot
160001017.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have no other monsters on your field, pay 500 LP.
[EFFECT]
Add 1 "Kuribot" from your Graveyard to your hand.

160001018.name: Whispering Fairy
160001018.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Shuffle up to 2 monsters from your opponent's Graveyard into the Deck.

160001019.name: Fire Golem
160001019.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Pay 600 LP.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up monster on your opponent's field loses 600 DEF until the end of this turn.

160001020.name: Hilt, the Bearer of Noble Arms
160001020.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
1 Attack Position Warrior Type monster on your field gains 600 ATK until the end of this turn.

160001022.name: Raidacross, Hero of the Dawn
160001022.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Shuffle 2 Spellcaster Type monsters from your Graveyard into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon up to 2 Level 5 or lower Spellcaster Type monsters face-up from your hand to your field.

160001024.name: Sportsdragon Pitcher
160001024.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have no other monsters on your field.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 "Sportsdragon Slugger" from your Graveyard to your field in face-up Defense Position. This turn, your Level 6 and lower monsters cannot attack.

160001025.name: Sportsdragon Slugger
160001025.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have no other monsters on your field.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 "Sportsdragon Pitcher" from your Graveyard to your field in face-up Defense Position. This turn, your Level 6 and lower monsters cannot attack.

160001026.name: Dragonic Slayer
160001026.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have a face-up Level 7 or higher Dragon Type monster other than this card on your field.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 Spell/Trap Card on your opponent's field.

160001028.name: Prima Guitarna the Shining Superstar
160001028.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Pay 1000 LP.
[EFFECT]
All face-up monsters on your field gain ATK equal to [the number of monsters on your opponent's field] x 300 until the end of this turn.

160001029.name: Yamiruler the Dark Delayer
160001029.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During the turn you Normal Summoned this card, change its battle position (Attack Position becomes face-up Defense Position, Defense Position becomes face-up Attack Position).
[EFFECT]
Until the end of the opponent's next turn, while this card is face-up, neither player can Tribute Summon Level 7 or higher monsters.

160001030.name: Spice the Elite Noodle Ninja
160001030.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
All face-up Pyro Type monsters on your field gain ATK equal to [the number of Normal Monsters in your Graveyard] x 100 until the end of this turn.

160001031.name: Defender of Dragon Sorcerers
160001031.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 Spellcaster or Dragon Type monster from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
1 monster on your field cannot be destroyed by an opponent's card effect this turn.

160001032.name: Thunder the Thunder
160001032.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up monster on your opponent's field loses 300 ATK until the end of this turn.

160001033.name: Sonic Attacker
160001033.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Your opponent gains 1000 LP. This card gains 1000 ATK until the end of this turn.

160001034.name: Mask of Volos
160001034.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Change the original ATK of 1 face-up Level 6 or lower monster on your opponent's field to 1500 until the end of this turn.

160001035.name: Diabolic King Beetle
160001035.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up monster on your field gains ATK equal to [the number of Level 1 monsters in your Graveyard] x 100 until the end of this turn.

160001036.name: Battle Shark Samegalon
160001036.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 WATER Attribute monster from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Change 1 Defense Position monster on your opponent's field to face-up Attack Position.

160001037.name: Pierce!
160001037.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Choose 1 face-up monster on your field. If it attacks a Defense Position monster this turn, inflict piercing battle damage (if the ATK of the attacking monster exceeds the DEF of the attack target, inflict the difference).

160001038.name: Recovery Force
160001038.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Shuffle 3 Spellcaster Type monsters from your Graveyard into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
Draw 1 card.

160001039.name: Road Magic - Tempest
160001039.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have a face-up Level 7 or higher Spellcaster Type monster on your field, send 1 WIND Attribute monster from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Change the battle position of up to 3 monsters on your opponent's field (Attack Position becomes face-up Defense Position, Defense Position becomes face-up Attack Position).

160001040.name: Seal of the Ancients (Rush)
160001040.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Pay 1000 LP.
[EFFECT]
Look at all face-down cards on your opponent's field, then return them to their original positions.

160001041.name: Hammer Crush
160001041.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 Spell/Trap Card on your opponent's field.

160001042.name: Sparks (Rush)
160001042.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Inflict 200 damage to your opponent.

160001043.name: Darkness Approaches (Rush)
160001043.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 2 cards from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Change 1 face-up monster on either side of the field to face-down Defense Position.

160001044.name: One-Side Reverse
160001044.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Your opponent has 2 or more face-down monsters on their field.
[EFFECT]
Change 1 face-down monster on your opponent's field to face-up Attack Position.

160001045.name: Mountain (Rush)
160001045.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
While this card is face-up in the Field Zone, face-up Dragon, Winged Beast, and Thunder Type monsters on the field gain 200 ATK/DEF.

160001046.name: Counter Cannonball
160001046.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When an opponent's monster declares an attack, send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Inflict damage to your opponent equal to [the Level of the attacking monster] x 200.

160001047.name: Call of the Earthbound (Rush)
160001047.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When an opponent's monster declares an attack.
[EFFECT]
You choose which of your monsters becomes the attack target for your opponent's attack.

160001048.name: Gust (Rush)
160001048.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When a Spell Card on your field is destroyed by an opponent's card effect.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 Spell/Trap Card on either side of the field.

160001049.name: Brutal Retribution
160001049.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When 2 or more face-up Normal Monsters on your field are destroyed at the same time by an opponent's card effect.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon up to 2 monsters from your Graveyard face-up to your field.

160001050.name: 1-Up
160001050.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When a monster(s) on your field is destroyed by an opponent's attack or their card effect.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Level 1 Normal Monster from your Graveyard face-up to your field.

160002000.name: Dark Magician (Rush)
160002000.description: The ultimate wizard in terms of attack and defense.

160002001.name: Sportsdragon Keeper
160002001.description: A clutch player for the team. No matter what flies at him, he will risk his life to stop it.

160002002.name: Wattkiss
160002002.description: Blows kisses that leave you tingling. They get the feeling across.

160002003.name: Watangel
160002003.description: A guitar that has descended to the lower realm. The tones it plays are angelic.

160002004.name: Mammoth Graveyard (Rush)
160002004.description: A mammoth that protects the graves of its pack and is absolutely merciless when facing grave-robbers.

160002005.name: Megazowler (Rush)
160002005.description: Nothing stands in the way of this spike-covered dinosaur!

160002006.name: Bubbly Elf
160002006.description: This girl is delicate no more. While poised and collected, she's always down to party. Pager pals with LaMoon the Party Princess.

160002007.name: LaMoon the Party Princess
160002007.description: A sorceress that has escaped dull, everyday life. She uses lunar magic to captivate affluent men. Besties with Kanan the Sword Diva.

160002008.name: Kanan the Sword Diva
160002008.description: A swordswoman who leads the vanguard in the entertainment district. Even in full makeup, she always carries her sword and shield. Friends with Bubbly Elf.

160002009.name: Beast Gear Gyro Jackal
160002009.description: A beast that drives around wildly, always in search of some fun. He is petty, and only picks fights he thinks he can win, so he often falls to unexpected counterattacks. He grows uninhibited when he's got friends around, which leads to misunderstandings, and he still hasn't figured out that he can't do anything on his own.

160002010.name: Beast Gear Buggy Dog
160002010.description: A canine that extorts scraps of dog food from an old man. He is full of himself and acts tough, but has no real convictions. He used to hate living life on a leash, but now he feels that he was happier just to have an owner.

160002011.name: Beast Gear Moto Wolf
160002011.description: A beast continually looting citizens of their food and gasoline. He might appear to be a lone wolf, but he believes that evil is right and does everything he can for his gang. For such a wicked criminal, one can't help but wonder why his distant howls touch the heart so deeply.

160002012.name: Jet Barracuda
160002012.description: This creature uses jet propulsion to charge in shocking speeds. Some wonder whether it even is a fish.

160002013.name: Heat Dartfish
160002013.description: A fish with a proboscis that heats up when attacking. Its mild flavor makes it a true delicacy.

160002014.name: Harpie Girl (Rush)
160002014.description: A Harpie chick who aspires to flit about beautifully and gorgeously, but attack sharply.

160002015.name: Vishwar Randi (Rush)
160002015.description: This lady warrior with unquenchable bloodlust serves the forces of darkness.

160002016.name: Sevens Road Mage
160002016.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up Level 7 or higher monster on your opponent's field loses 400 ATK until the end of this turn. Then, it loses additional [number of Spellcaster Type monsters in your Graveyard] x 100 ATK until the end of this turn, if you have "Sevens Road Magician" face-up on your field.

160002017.name: Lightning Voltcondor
160002017.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 monster from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
All face-up monsters on your opponent's field with the same Attribute as the monster sent to the Graveyard to meet the requirement lose ATK/DEF equal to [the Level of that monster sent to the Graveyard] x 300 until the end of this turn.

160002018.name: Full Meteor Impact
160002018.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have a face-up Level 7 or higher Spellcaster Type monster on your field during the turn you Normal Summoned this card, send this face-up card from your field to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Destroy all face-up Level 6 or higher monsters on your opponent's field.

160002019.name: Sportsdragon Defender
160002019.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have "Sportsdragon Keeper" on your field in Attack Position, send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Change 1 Attack Position "Sportsdragon Keeper" on your field and 1 Attack Position monster on your opponent's field to face-up Defense Position.

160002020.name: Sportsdragon Striker
160002020.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have "Sportsdragon Keeper" face-up on your field, send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This turn, 1 face-up monster on your field gains 400 ATK, and if it attacks a Defense Position monster, inflict piercing battle damage (if the ATK of the attacking monster exceeds the DEF of the attack target, inflict the difference).

160002021.name: Shock Dragon
160002021.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Until the end of this turn, all face-up monsters with the highest ATK on your opponent's field lose ATK equal to [the ATK of the face-up monster with the highest ATK on your field]. This card can only attack Attack Position monsters this turn.

160002022.name: Piercing Dragon Bunker Strike
160002022.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard during the turn you Normal Summoned this card.
[EFFECT]
Draw cards equal to [the number of monsters on your opponent's field], then place cards from your hand equal to [the number of cards drawn by this effect] on either the top or bottom of the Deck in any order.

160002023.name: Romanpick
160002023.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If your LP are lower than your opponent's, pay 500 LP.
[EFFECT]
Send the top 3 cards of your Deck to the Graveyard. If a Psychic Type monster(s) is among the cards sent, add 1 Psychic Type monster from the Graveyard to your hand.

160002024.name: Romic n' Roller
160002024.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Your LP are 2000 or lower.
[EFFECT]
All face-up monsters on your opponent's field lose 500 ATK and DEF until the end of this turn.

160002025.name: Esperade the Smashing Superstar
160002025.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Your LP are 1000 or lower.
[EFFECT]
Destroy up to 2 monsters on your opponent's field.

160002026.name: Nandes the Fire Awakener
160002026.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Change 1 face-up Defense Position Warrior Type monster on your field to Attack Position.

160002027.name: Dian Keto the Boogie Master
160002027.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Gain 1000 LP.

160002028.name: Beast Gear Emperor Catapult Kong
160002028.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send up to 2 face-up Beast-Warrior Type monsters other than this card from your field to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Destroy Defense Position monsters on your opponent's field equal to [the number of monsters sent to the Graveyard to meet the requirement].

160002029.name: Super King Rex
160002029.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During your Main Phase that you Normal or Special Summoned this card, send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Level 6 or lower Dinosaur Type Normal Monster from your Graveyard face-up to your field.

160002030.name: Wicked Shadow Dark Lurker
160002030.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 Spell/Trap Card on your opponent's field and if you do, inflict 1000 damage to your opponent. Then, return this card to the owner's hand.

160002031.name: Royal Rebel's Heavy Metal
160002031.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During the turn you Normal Summoned this card by Tributing a Level 5 or higher monster.
[EFFECT]
Choose 1 face-up Level 8 or lower monster with the lowest Level on your opponent's field, and this card gains ATK equal to [that monster's ATK] until the end of this turn. Destroy that monster.

160002032.name: Hydro Cannon Big Bluefin
160002032.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Up to 2 face-up Fish Type monsters on your field with 1000 or less ATK can attack directly this turn.

160002033.name: Archfiend's Summoning Flute
160002033.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have no other monsters on your field and have 3 or more Normal Monsters in your Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Send this card from your field to the Graveyard, then Special Summon 1 Normal Monster from your Graveyard to your field in face-up Defense Position.

160002034.name: Shaman Octopus
160002034.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Pay 800 LP.
[EFFECT]
This card gains ATK equal to [the Level of 1 Normal Monster in your Graveyard] x 100 until the end of this turn. Then, shuffle that monster into your Deck.

160002035.name: Innocent Lancer
160002035.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
If this card attacks a Defense Position monster this turn, inflict piercing battle damage (if the ATK of the attacking monster exceeds the DEF of the attack target, inflict the difference).

160002036.name: Road Magic - Tectonic Shift
160002036.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have a face-up Level 7 or higher Spellcaster Type monster on your field, send 1 EARTH Attribute monster from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up monster on your opponent's field loses ATK equal to [the ATK of the monster with the highest ATK in your Graveyard] until the end of this turn.

160002037.name: Lullabind
160002037.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have 2 or more face-up Psychic Type monsters on your field.
[EFFECT]
Change 1 face-up monster on your opponent's field to face-down Defense Position.

160002038.name: Party Party Party
160002038.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Change all Attack Position Aqua Type monsters on your field to face-up Defense Position, and gain LP equal to [the number of monsters changed to face-up Defense Position by this effect] x 400.

160002039.name: Apocalypse - Beast Gear World
160002039.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
While this card is face-up in the Field Zone, face-up Beast-Warrior, Fiend, and Machine Type monsters on the field gain 300 ATK, and face-up Dragon, Spellcaster, and Fairy Type monsters on the field lose 300 ATK.

160002040.name: Thousand Knives (Rush)
160002040.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have "Dark Magician" face-up on your field.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 monster on your opponent's field.

160002041.name: Dark Magic Attack (Rush)
160002041.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have "Dark Magician" face-up on your field.
[EFFECT]
Destroy all Spell/Trap Cards on your opponent's field.

160002042.name: Blades of Divine Wind
160002042.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Destroy 2 face-up Normal Monsters on your field and 1 face-up Level 8 or lower monster on your opponent's field.

160002043.name: Attribute Shift Bomb
160002043.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Reveal 1 monster in your hand to your opponent.
[EFFECT]
This turn, the Attributes of up to 3 face-up monsters on your opponent's field become the same as the monster revealed to meet the requirement.

160002045.name: Party Time - Disco Ball
160002045.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent Normal Summons a Level 5 or higher monster.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Aqua Type monster from your Graveyard face-up to your field.

160002046.name: Rage and Conspiracy
160002046.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent Normal Summons a monster while you have 2 or more different Types of Normal Monster(s) on your field.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 face-up Level 6 or lower monster on your opponent's field.

160002047.name: Siesta Hold
160002047.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent Normal Summons a Level 4 or lower monster while they have no other monsters on their field.
[EFFECT]
Change that monster to face-down Defense Position.

160002048.name: Phantom Bind
160002048.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When an opponent's monster declares an attack.
[EFFECT]
The attacking monster loses ATK equal to [the number of monsters with its same Type in your opponent's Graveyard] x 100 until the end of this turn.

160002049.name: Double Block
160002049.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When an opponent's monster declares an attack, send 2 Level 2 Normal Monsters from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Change up to 2 face-up monsters on your opponent's field to face-down Defense Position.

160002050.name: Driving Snow (Rush)
160002050.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When a Trap Card(s) on your field is destroyed by an opponent's card effect.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 Spell/Trap Card on either side of the field.

160003000.name: Summoned Skull (Rush)
160003000.description: A fiend with dark powers for confusing the enemy. Among the Fiend Type monsters, this monster boasts considerable force.

160003001.name: Light Sorcerer
160003001.description: A spellcaster who has devoted himself to the heavens. He is wreathed in divine blessings, but what fate awaits him?

160003002.name: Scoop Scooter
160003002.description: Delivers the morning edition before breakfast! Also delivers the evening edition before breakfast!

160003003.name: Stock the Noodle Ninja
160003003.description: A ninja who prides himself on being al dente. He constantly trains himself to reach the hardness of steel wire. He isn't great with water techniques.

160003004.name: Mushroom Man (Rush)
160003004.description: Found in humid regions, this creature attacks enemies with a lethal rain of poison spores.

160003005.name: Niwatori (Rush)
160003005.description: Swallows enemies whole and uses their essence as energy.

160003006.name: Chu-Ske the Mouse Fighter (Rush)
160003006.description: A fiery mouse, travelling the world to become the strongest fighter in the world of mice. Be careful not to touch him, or you will get burned.

160003007.name: Baby Dragon (Rush)
160003007.description: Much more than just a child, this dragon is gifted with untapped power.

160003008.name: Hitotsu-Me Giant (Rush)
160003008.description: A one-eyed behemoth with thick, powerful arms made for delivering punishing blows.

160003009.name: Doriado (Rush)
160003009.description: A spirit of the forest powered by the surrounding trees and wildlife.

160003010.name: Water Magician (Rush)
160003010.description: This monster swamps an opponent with an almost endless supply of water.

160003011.name: Gazelle the King of Mythical Beasts (Rush)
160003011.description: This monster moves so fast that it looks like an illusion to mortal eyes.

160003012.name: Ojisan
160003012.description: A tired old fish that can't seem to get rid of his aches.

160003013.name: Echeclus the Star Knight
160003013.description: A man who carries the power of an evil star. He charges across the battlefield each day, filled with faith in his own sense of justice.

160003014.name: Sparkhearts Girl
160003014.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 Level 4 or lower monster from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up monster on your opponent's field loses 500 ATK until the end of this turn. Then, you can Set 1 "Sparks" and/or 1 "Curtain of Sparks" from your Graveyard in your Spell & Trap Zone.

160003015.name: Silver Wolf
160003015.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have a face-up Beast Type monster on your field other than this card, send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up monster on your opponent's field loses 200 ATK/DEF until the end of this turn.

160003016.name: Beast Summoner
160003016.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If your opponent has a face-up Level 6 or higher monster on their field, send this face-up card from your field to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Level 7 or lower Beast, Beast-Warrior, or Winged Beast Type monster from your hand to your field, face-up.

160003017.name: Sieth, the Scabbard of Noble Arms
160003017.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Place 4 Warrior and/or Spellcaster Type monsters from your Graveyard on the bottom of your Deck in any order.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Level 7 Warrior Type monster from your hand face-up to your field.

160003018.name: Bendorbreak the Conqueror
160003018.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If [the number of face-up monsters on your opponent's field] and [the number of Spell/Trap Cards on your field] are the same, send up to 3 Spell/Trap Cards from your field to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up monster on your opponent's field loses ATK/DEF equal to [the number of cards sent to the Graveyard to meet the requirement] x 1000 until the end of this turn.

160003019.name: Savage Claw Tiger
160003019.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]

160004000.name: Jinzo (Rush)
160004000.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[CONTINUOUS EFFECT]
Neither player can activate Trap Cards, and all Trap Card effects are negated.

160004001.name: Constructor Soldier Drillzard
160004001.description: A humanoid reincarnated from a dragon. His masterful strategy and deft hands help reduce construction times considerably.

160004002.name: Constructor Warrior Shovelon
160004002.description: A young warrior. Each day he passionately uses his shovel to dig up work sites.

160004003.name: Constructor Battler Big Roller
160004003.description: A veteran warrior. He uses six types of rollers in his work, but laymen cannot tell the difference between them.

160004004.name: Brassaxophone the Music Princess
160004004.description: The heart and soul of the band. Her dynamic tones make her an excellent solo fighter, but she needs help to equip the weapon on her left arm.

160004005.name: Flutomahawk the Music Princess
160004005.description: The vanguard of the band. She creates beautiful melodies by swinging her axes through the air. Some believe she chooses her outfit to hide her weaponry, but it's just because she gets cold easily.

160004006.name: Bull Breaker
160004006.description: Incredibly useful on site, but the lease is exorbitant. Planning is the biggest part of the job.

160004007.name: Oppressed Ant
160004007.description: An ant who is oppressed, but believes it will have freedom someday.

160004008.name: United Ants
160004008.description: Ants that gather to swear to fight their oppressors. A revolution is coming.

160004009.name: Ants Running About
160004009.description: Although they always suffer in silence, they swear an oath to inevitably revolt.

160004010.name: Tsuvolcano
160004010.description: Here comes a magma-hot shiatsu massage! Pressure Point Eruption!

160004011.name: Enchanting Mermaid (Rush)
160004011.description: A beautiful mermaid that lures voyagers to a watery grave.

160004012.name: Descendant of Titans
160004012.description: A successor of old gods. Skilled at hiding, few know of their existence.

160004014.name: Silent Assailant
160004014.description: An elusive assassin who undertakes dangerous missions while searching for her lost partner.

160004015.name: Steel Mech Lord Mirror Innovator

None
[EFFECT]
Choose up to 3 monsters in your Graveyard with the same Type as this card. This card gains ATK equal to [the total Levels of those monsters] x 100 until the end of this turn. Then, shuffle those monsters into the Deck. If you shuffled exactly 1 monster by this effect, this card inflicts piercing battle damage (if the ATK of the attacking monster exceeds the DEF of the attack target, inflict the difference), if it attacks a Defense Position monster this turn.

When your opponent Normal Summons a Level 5 or higher monster.
[EFFECT]
Change the battle position of 1 face-up Machine Type monster on your field (Attack Position becomes face-up Defense Position, Defense Position becomes face-up Attack Position). If you do, that monster on your field gains 1500 ATK until the end of this turn.

160004056.name: Gi-ant Revolution
160004056.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent's monster declares an attack while you have 3 face-up Insect Type monsters with 100 or less ATK on your field.
[EFFECT]
Destroy all face-up Level 8 or lower monsters on your opponent's field.

160004057.name: Antiberty Flag
160004057.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent Normal or Special Summons a monster.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Insect Type monster with 100 or less ATK from your hand or your Graveyard face-up to your field.

160004058.name: Earth Pressure Explosion
160004058.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When an Attack Position Pyro Type monster(s) on your field is destroyed by an opponent's attack or their Trap Card effect.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 "Magmassage" or 1 "Magmax Mantleveda" from your Graveyard face-up to your field. Then, if you have an EARTH Attribute Pyro Type monster in your Graveyard, gain 1000 LP.

160004059.name: Jewelry Trap Hole
160004059.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent Normal or Special Summons a monster while you have 3 face-up Aqua Type monsters on your field.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 face-up Level 8 or lower monster on your opponent's field.

160004060.name: Beast Gear Secret Art - Primal Fist
160004060.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When an opponent's monster declares an attack targeting your face-up Level 7-9 Beast-Warrior, Fiend, or Machine Type monster.
[EFFECT]
Change the attacking monster to face-up Defense Position. Then, if you changed a Dragon, Spellcaster, or Fairy Type monster to Defense Position by this effect, you can destroy 1 Spell/Trap Card on your opponent's field.

160005000.name: Buster Blader (Rush)
160005000.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[CONTINUOUS EFFECT]
This card gains ATK equal to [the number of Dragon Type monsters on your opponent's field and in their Graveyard] x500.

160005001.name: The Fire Dragon
160005001.description: A very beautiful dragon covered with FIRE. It does not like fights, but has incredibly high attack power.

160005002.name: CAN:D
160005002.description: Carrying infinite potential, she continues to chase her shining dream with a smile on her face.

160005003.name: Royal Rebel's No Wave
160005003.description: A bizarre demonic devil who serves the King. It absorbs every sound and repels every attack.

160005004.name: Guarding Mermaid
160005004.description: A fierce mermaid that torments the damned who fell to hell. She has a great reputation of making recidivists beg "I will never do anything bad again, please forgive me".

160005005.name: Kanan the Security Guard
160005005.description: A lady warrior whose main battlefield is a prison island. Armed with sword and shield, she rebukes harshly. She has a great reputation of bringing recidivists back to their senses.

160005006.name: Kurobana the Shadow Flower Wolf
160005006.description: A group of grass ninjas who protect their lord from crises, while concealed in the shadow. Even if they are struck down, they strike back from the shadows of blades of grass.

160005007.name: Lindo the Shadow Flower Warrior
160005007.description: A group of grass ninjas who secretly support the path to victory while concealing themselves in the shadows. They continue to loyally serve their lord.

160005008.name: Bombing Bird
160005008.description: A bird that drops bombs. There may be a tiny person inside.

160005010.name: Surge Bolt Lizard
160005010.description: An electric lifeform that appears with lightning strikes. It can transform itself into an electric current that invades circuitry, causing machinery to fail.

160005011.name: Baked Bean Soldier
160005011.description: A surprisingly hot plant-warrior that attacks with seeds and sword.

160005012.name: Metal Armored Ant
160005012.description: A gigantic ant-like creature covered by thick armor. Everything in its path that tries to harm the forest will be blocked.

160005013.name: Ice Age Catapult
160005013.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During the turn you Normal Summoned this card, place 1 WATER Attribute monster from your Graveyard on the bottom of the Deck.
[EFFECT]
Return 1 Spell/Trap Card from your opponent's field to the hand. Then, you can make 1 face-up monster on your opponent's field lose 600 ATK/DEF until the end of this turn.

160005014.name: Hyper Engine Vast Vulcan [L]
160005014.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Maximum Mode: Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up monster on your opponent's field loses 800 ATK until the end of this turn. Then, you can destroy a Field Spell Card on your opponent's field. Then, if you destroyed a Field Spell Card by this effect, inflict 800 damage to your opponent.

160005015.name: Hyper Engine Vast Vulcan
160005015.description:
MAXIMUM ATK = 3300
Can be Maximum Summoned together with "Hyper Engine Vast Vulcan [L]" and "Hyper Engine Vast Vulcan [R]".

[REQUIREMENT]
Maximum Mode
[CONTINUOUS EFFECT]
This card cannot be destroyed by your opponent's Trap effects.

160005016.name: Hyper Engine Vast Vulcan [R]
160005016.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Maximum Mode: Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up monster on either side of the field loses ATK equal to [its Level] x 100 until the end of this turn. Then, inflict damage to your opponent equal to [that monster's Level] x 100.

160005017.name: Fortitude Dragon
160005017.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You can send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up monster with 2000 or more ATK on your opponent's field loses 400 ATK until the end of this turn. Then, you can Set 1 "Dragon's Fortitude" from your Graveyard in your Spell & Trap Zone.

160005018.name: Endoll
160005018.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 monster from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Send this card from your field to the Graveyard. Then, you can Set up to 2 "Climax Finale" and/or "Psychic Introduction" from your Graveyard in your Spell & Trap Zone.

160005019.name: CAN - Re:D
160005019.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Return 1 face-up monster with 500 or less ATK from your field to the hand. This turn, while this card is face-up, you cannot Tribute Summon monsters with 1500 or more DEF in Attack Position.

160005020.name: Takegumi the Ruler's Squad
160005020.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If your opponent has a monster on their field and you have a monster with 0 ATK in your Graveyard, send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up monster on your field gains ATK equal to [the number of monsters with 0 ATK in your Graveyard] x 200 until the end of this turn.

160005021.name: Wondering Warrior
160005021.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During the turn you Normal Summoned this card, send this face-up card from your field to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon up to 2 Warrior and/or Winged Beast Type Normal Monsters from your Graveyard to your field in face-down Defense Position.

160005022.name: Icezark the Unequaled
160005022.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Place 2 Level 7 or higher Warrior Type monsters with different names from your Graveyard on the bottom of the Deck in any order.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Level 7 or higher Warrior Type monster from your Graveyard face-up to your field.

160005023.name: Royal Rebel's Phaser
160005023.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have a face-up Level 7 or higher Fiend Type monster on your field, send this face-up card from your field to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Level 7 or higher Fiend Type monster from your Graveyard to your field in face-up Defense Position.

160005024.name: Royal Rebel's Doom Metal
160005024.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During the turn this card was Normal Summoned by Tributing 2 Level 7 or higher Fiend Type monsters.
[EFFECT]
Destroy all face-up monsters on your opponent's field, then inflict damage to your opponent equal to [the total original Levels of the monsters destroyed by this effect] x 100.

160005025.name: Vice Jacker
160005025.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Pay 1000 LP.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up Level 8 DARK Attribute monster on your field can make a second attack this turn.

160005026.name: Dian Keto the Security Master
160005026.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Look at your opponent's hand and send 1 card from it to the Graveyard. If you sent a Level 7 or higher monster to the Graveyard by this effect, gain 1000 LP.

160005027.name: Acacia the Shadow Flower Priestess
160005027.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have a face-up Level 7 or higher Plant Type monster on your field.
[EFFECT]
Change 1 Defense Position monster on your opponent's field to face-up Attack Position. Then, if you changed a monster to face-up Attack Position by this effect, gain LP equal to [that monster's original ATK].

160005028.name: Gekka the Shadow Flower Beauty
160005028.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During the turn you Normal Summoned this card, pay 500 LP.
[EFFECT]
Add 1 EARTH Attribute Plant Type Normal Monster from your Graveyard to your hand.

160005029.name: Etraynze the Shadow Flower Ninja
160005029.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have "Etraynze the Shadow Flower Ninja" in your Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Send 1 Plant Type monster from your hand to the Graveyard. Then, Special Summon 1 "Etraynze the Shadow Flower Ninja" from your Graveyard face-up to your field, but place it on the bottom of the Deck during the End Phase. This turn, this card cannot attack directly.

160005030.name: Gajumaru the Shadow Flower Lion
160005030.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 other face-up EARTH Attribute Plant Type monster from your field to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Change the original ATK of 1 face-up Level 8 or lower EARTH Attribute monster on your opponent's field to 0 until the end of this turn.

160005031.name: Garland the True Shadow Flower Ninja
160005031.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Place 1 Plant Type monster from your Graveyard on the bottom of the Deck.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Level 7 or lower Plant Type monster from your hand face-up to your field, but place it on the bottom of the Deck during the End Phase.

160005032.name: Gatling the Shadow Flower Shinobi
160005032.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 2 Plant Type Normal Monsters from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Destroy up to 2 face-up Attack Position Level 8 or lower monsters on your opponent's field. Then, inflict damage to your opponent equal to [the number of monsters destroyed by this effect] x 500. This turn, you can only attack with 1 monster.

160005033.name: Blasting Bird
160005033.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Reveal 2 Spell/Trap Cards in your hand.
[EFFECT]
This turn, this face-up card can be treated as 2 Tributes for the Tribute Summon of a Winged Beast Type monster in Attack Position.

160005034.name: Night Vision the Phantom Pigeon
160005034.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have a Trap Card in your Graveyard, send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This card gains ATK equal to [the number of Trap Cards in your Graveyard] x 200 until the end of this turn. Then, if you have 5 or more Trap Cards in your Graveyard, inflict 1000 damage to your opponent.

160005035.name: Siesta Torero
160005035.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Shuffle 3 monsters from your Graveyard into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
Change 1 Attack Position Level 8 or lower monster on your opponent's field to face-down Defense Position. Then, if you changed a monster to face-down Defense Position by this effect, you can add 1 "Siesta Hold" from your Graveyard to your hand.

160005036.name: Maginical Miracle
160005036.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have a face-up monster with 100 ATK/100 DEF on your field, send this face-up card from your field to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Level 7 Psychic Type monster from your Graveyard to your field in face-up Attack Position.

160005037.name: Coiled Dragon of Fertility
160005037.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Shuffle 1 Field Spell Card from your Graveyard into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
Inflict 600 damage to your opponent.

160005038.name: Kheiron the Star Knight
160005038.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If your opponent has a monster on their field, send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Choose 1 face-up Level 5 or higher Fiend Type monster on your field. If it attacks a Defense Position monster this turn, inflict piercing battle damage (if the ATK of the attacking monster exceeds the DEF of the attack target, inflict the difference).

160005039.name: JAM:P Up!
160005039.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 face-up Psychic Type monster from your field to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Level 7 Psychic Type monster from your hand face-up to your field. If you sent "CAN:D" to the Graveyard to meet the requirement, the monster Special Summoned by this effect gains 1500 ATK until the end of this turn.

160005040.name: JAM:P Start!
160005040.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Place 2 Psychic Type monsters from your Graveyard on the bottom of the Deck in any order.
[EFFECT]
Add 1 Psychic Type Normal Monster from your Graveyard to your hand. Then, if you added "CAN:D" to your hand by this effect, gain 1000 LP.

160005041.name: Royal Rebel's Command
160005041.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 Fiend Type monster from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up LIGHT Attribute Fiend Type monster on your field gains 1000 ATK until the end of this turn, then you can change its battle position (Attack Position becomes face-up Defense Position, Defense Position becomes face-up Attack Position).

160005042.name: Royal Rebel's Arena
160005042.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Activate this card if your opponent controls 2 or more monsters.
[EFFECT]
While this card is face-up in the Field Zone, face-up LIGHT Attribute Fiend Type monsters on the field cannot be destroyed by Trap Card effects.

160005043.name: Transmigration of Curiosity
160005043.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Shuffle 4 monsters with 100 or less DEF from your Graveyard into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
Draw 1 card.

160005044.name: Mighty Gaze of the Sky Emperor
160005044.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 monster from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Change the battle position of 1 monster on your opponent's field (Attack Position becomes face-up Defense Position, Defense Position becomes face-up Attack Position). Then, if you have a face-up Level 10 monster on your field, you can draw 1 card.

160005045.name: Prison Island - Cell Block 5 & 6
160005045.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
While this card is face-up in the Field Zone, neither player can Tribute Summon Level 5 or 6 monsters.

160005046.name: Last Day of the Pretty☆Witch
160005046.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have a face-up Level 8 or higher Aqua Type monster on your field, send 1 Aqua Type monster from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 face-up Level 8 or lower monster on your opponent's field. Then, if you destroyed a Spellcaster Type monster by this effect, you can destroy all monsters on your opponent's field.

160005047.name: Hydration
160005047.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have 2 or more face-up Aqua Type monsters on your field.
[EFFECT]
Gain 500 LP. Then, if you gained LP by this effect, you can destroy 1 Spell/Trap Card on your opponent's field.

160005048.name: Shadow Flower Spore
160005048.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have a Level 4 or lower Plant Type Normal Monster in your Graveyard, send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Level 4 or lower Plant Type Normal Monster from your Graveyard face-up to your field, but place it on the bottom of the Deck during the End Phase.

160005049.name: Apocalypse - The Unstoppable Beast-Warrior
160005049.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have a face-up "Apocalypse - Beast Gear World" on your field, pay 1000 LP.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Beast-Warrior Type monster from your Graveyard to your field face-up. It inflicts piercing battle damage this turn.

160005050.name: Majinrai, the Striking Storm
160005050.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have a face-up "Summoned Skull" or a face-up Level 7 or higher Fiend Type Normal Monster on your field.
[EFFECT]
Send 1 Normal Monster from your hand to the Graveyard. Then, inflict 1300 damage to your opponent.

160005051.name: Invading Nature
160005051.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have a face-up Plant Type monster on your field.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 Spell/Trap Card on your opponent's field.

160005052.name: Judgment of the Rising Light
160005052.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Shuffle 1 monster from either Graveyard into the Deck. Then, if your opponent has no cards in their hand, you can return 1 face-up monster from your opponent's field to the hand.

160005053.name: Avian Spell Tactics
160005053.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have 2 or more face-up Warrior and/or Winged Beast Type monsters on your field.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 Spell/Trap Card on your opponent's field. Then, if you destroyed a Spell/Trap Card by this effect, you can place 1 Level 8 or lower Warrior or Winged Beast Type monster from your Graveyard on top of the Deck.

160005054.name: Wasteland (Rush)
160005054.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
While this card is face-up in the Field Zone, face-up Dinosaur, Zombie, and Rock Type monsters on the field gain 200 ATK/DEF.

160005055.name: Pretty☆Witch Imprisonment
160005055.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent Normal Summons a monster while you have a face-up Level 8 or higher Aqua Type monster on your field.
[EFFECT]
Shuffle up to 5 monsters from your opponent's Graveyard into the Deck. Then, if your opponent has a face-up Spellcaster Type monster on their field, you can shuffle up to 5 additional monsters from your opponent's Graveyard into the Deck.

160005056.name: All For Naught - Bubble Burst
160005056.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When an opponent's monster declares an attack targeting your face-up Level 8 or higher Aqua Type monster.
[EFFECT]
The attacking monster loses 600 ATK until the end of this turn. Then, if your opponent has a face-up Spellcaster Type monster on their field, 1 face-up monster on your opponent's field loses 1 million ATK until the end of this turn.

160005057.name: Shadow Flower Stance
160005057.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When an opponent's monster declares an attack targeting your face-up Plant Type monster, place 2 Plant Type monsters from your Graveyard on the bottom of the Deck in any order.
[EFFECT]
Change all Attack Position monsters on your opponent's field to face-up Defense Position.

160005058.name: Shadow Flower Return
160005058.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When an opponent's monster declares a direct attack, shuffle 3 Plant Type monsters from your Graveyard into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
Destroy the attacking monster. Then, if you destroyed a monster by this effect, you can Special Summon 1 Plant Type monster from your Graveyard to your field in face-up Attack Position.

160005059.name: Brocoohearted Pigeon
160005059.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent Normal or Special Summons a Level 5 or higher monster face-up while you have a face-up Winged Beast Type monster on your field.
[EFFECT]
Change 1 Attack Position monster on your opponent's field to face-up Defense Position. Then, if you changed a monster to face-up Defense Position by this effect, inflict 500 damage to your opponent.

160005060.name: Clowning Cookoo Clock
160005060.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent Normal Summons a monster and you have a face-up Winged Beast Type monster on your field.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 "Night Vision the Phantom Pigeon" from your Graveyard face-up to your field. Then, gain 1500 LP.

160005061.name: Music Princess's Recital
160005061.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When an opponent's Level 8 or lower monster declares an attack while you have exactly 1 monster on your field.
[EFFECT]
Negate the attack.

160005062.name: Archfiend's Revival
160005062.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your "Summoned Skull" or Level 7 or higher Fiend Type Normal Monster is destroyed by an opponent's attack.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Normal Monster from your Graveyard face-up to your field.

160005063.name: Maraimei, the Igniting Inferno
160005063.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent Normal or Special Summons a Level 6 or higher monster(s) face-up, and you have a face-up "Summoned Skull" or a face-up Level 7 or higher Fiend Type Normal Monster on your field.
[EFFECT]
You take damage equal to [the number of monsters in your opponent's Graveyard] x 100. Then, shuffle all monsters from your opponent's Graveyard into the Deck.

160005064.name: Cheering Grass
160005064.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent Normal Summons a monster.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Plant Type monster from your hand face-up to your field. Then, if you Special Summoned a Normal Monster by this effect, you can Special Summon up to 2 Level 1 Plant Type Normal Monsters from your Graveyard face-up to your field.

160005065.name: Acetic Acid Trap Hole
160005065.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent Normal Summons a Level 3 or lower Effect Monster.
[EFFECT]
Destroy that monster.

160006000.name: Cyber-Tech Alligator (Rush)
160006000.description: Originally a pterodactyl, he was viciously attacked by a dragon. Using the newest technologies, his keeper saved him from near-fatal wounds and brought him back as a powerful Cyborg.

160006001.name: Sunny Fairy Spinangel
160006001.description: An angel that's totally bringing the bling in the modern style. Nobody be stoppin' him, man.

160006002.name: Worker Warrior - New Recruit
160006002.description: A newbie drone that continues to update through trial and error. It operates on a frantic pace.

160006003.name: Worker Warrior - Bad Boss
160006003.description: A mid-level drone that allocates most of its memory to trying to get ahead in life. Its report is a storm filled with slander.

160006004.name: Barbeque Ox
160006004.description: A cattle monster with tremendously tasty tongue and stomach, it burns enemies with a swing of its skewer.

160006005.name: Mystic Roastman
160006005.description: Half man and half horse, this monster is known for its extreme dine and dashing.

160006006.name: Archfiend Marmot of Deliciousness
160006006.description: An air marmot that has a nefarious dipping sauce and dish. It attacks by throwing around popularity site rankings.

160006007.name: Hampering Hippo
160006007.description: An unexpectedly fast hippopotamus that pushes back against every attack. It can even use its treads to swim skillfully.

160006008.name: Dogulce Jomont Blanc
160006008.description: When a Mont Blanc was placed in Doki earthenware, a soul came to dwell within it. Screams of terror pour out at the sight of its form wandering the raised-floor-style warehouse area.

160006009.name: Pangoflame
160006009.description: A creature dwelling in a caldera, living at its own pace. While it remains calm, the flames covering its body cause everything around it to catch fire, turning the surrounding area into a sea of flames.

160006010.name: Flying Kamakiri #2 (Rush)
160006010.description: A flying mantis that feeds primarily on insects.

160006011.name: Northern Dumplina
160006011.description: The poster girl for a Northern Chinese restaurant who advocates for labor reforms. Many corporate warriors leave the office at the end of their shifts and come here to eat, but by that time, she's already gone home.

160006012.name: Fazuzu the King of Mythical Wind Beasts
160006012.description: A mythical beast with four wings. It secretly defends the royal capital.

160006013.name: Handy Lady
160006013.description: A jack-of-all-trades who'll take on any job, whether it be looking for lost cats to serving as a bodyguard for VIPs. Recently, she's been doing nothing but lunch delivery gigs, but one day, received a message from an unknown sender.

160006014.name: Sevens Road Wiz
160006014.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Change the original ATK of 1 face-up Level 8 or lower monster on your opponent's field with the same ATK as this card to 0 until the end of this turn. Then, if you have "Sevens Road Magician" in your Graveyard, you can draw 1 card.

160006015.name: Thunderbold, the Blazing Thunder
160006015.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During the turn this card was Normal Summoned, send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This card gains 300 ATK until the end of this turn. Then, if you have 4 or more Level 7 monsters with different names in your Graveyard, you can Special Summon 1 Level 7 monster from your Graveyard to your field face-up.

160006016.name: Stock Buster Dragon
160006016.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If your opponent has 5 or more cards on their field, send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
All face-up Level 7 or lower monsters on your opponent's field lose 1500 ATK until the end of this turn.

160006017.name: Steel Strike Dragon Metagias
160006017.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 Level 7 or higher Dragon Type monster from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This turn, this card cannot be destroyed by battle or your opponent's Trap effects, also it can make a second attack on a monster during the Battle Phase in which it attacked a monster.

160006018.name: Speedy Performer
160006018.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If your opponent has a monster on their field, send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up monster on your field gains 400 ATK until the end of this turn.

160006019.name: Future Diviner
160006019.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have a face-up Level 7 or higher Psychic Type monster on your field.
[EFFECT]
Draw 1 card, then send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.

160006020.name: Betrayer of Peace
160006020.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Change 1 Attack Position Warrior Type monster on the field to face-up Defense Position.

160006021.name: Karchizark the Unequaled
160006021.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 Level 7 or higher monster from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This card gains 1000 ATK until the end of this turn. Then, if you sent a Warrior or Winged Beast Type monster to the Graveyard by this effect's requirement, you can add 1 Level 6 or lower Normal Monster from your Graveyard to your hand.

160006022.name: Air Formula Eagle
160006022.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have 3 or more WIND Normal Monsters in your Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 WIND Normal Monster from your hand to your field face-up, then you can Special Summon 1 Level 6 or lower WIND Normal Monster from your Graveyard to your field face-up.

160006023.name: Secret Service Shine Guard
160006023.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During your Main Phase in which this card was Normal or Special Summoned, pay 600 LP.
[EFFECT]
Set up to 1 each of "Business Card Barrage" and "Nutrient Zero" from your Graveyard to your Spell & Trap Zone. This turn, you cannot attack with non-Machine Type monsters.

160006024.name: Worker Warrior - Sinister CEO
160006024.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If your opponent has a face-up Level 7 or higher monster on their field, send 1 monster from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Set up to 1 each of "Salary Slash" and "Battle Demotion" from your Graveyard to your Spell & Trap Zone.

160006025.name: Shichirin Samurai - Kushiro the Skewer Master
160006025.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During your Main Phase in which this card was Normal or Special Summoned, if you have 7 or more FIRE monsters in your Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Destroy all face-up Level 8 or lower monsters with 2500 or more ATK on your opponent's field.

160006026.name: Beast Drive Mega Elephant
160006026.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have a Level 6 or lower Beast Type Normal Monster in your Graveyard, send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Level 6 or lower Beast Type Normal Monster from your Graveyard to your field face-up. Then, if you have 3 or more Beast Type Normal Monsters in your Graveyard, you can draw 1 card.

160006027.name: Dogulce Langue de Shakoki
160006027.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During the turn this card was Normal Summoned.
[EFFECT]
Send the top 3 cards of your Deck to the Graveyard. Then, if there is a Pyro Type monster among them, you can add 1 Level 6 or higher Pyro Type monster from your Graveyard to your hand.

160006028.name: Doki Doki Hexenhaus
160006028.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During the turn this card was Normal Summoned.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Pyro Type Normal Monster from your Graveyard to your field face-up.

160006029.name: Jasmine the Shadow Flower Festival
160006029.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have a face-up Plant Type Normal Monster on your field.
[EFFECT]
Change 1 Defense Position monster on your opponent's field to face-up Attack Position. Then, if the monster changed to face-up Attack Position by this effect was EARTH, you can draw 1 card.

160006030.name: Crafter Drone
160006030.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 Machine Type monster from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Draw 1 card.

160006031.name: Assault Cannon
160006031.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have 3 face-up Machine Type monsters on your field, send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up monster on your opponent's field loses 300 ATK/DEF until the end of this turn.

160006032.name: Heat Hyena
160006032.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have no other monsters on your field.
[EFFECT]
Send cards from the top of your Deck to the Graveyard equal to [the number of monsters on your opponent's field].

160006033.name: Reset Runner
160006033.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Shuffle your Deck.

160006034.name: Lindmühle
160006034.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If a face-up Field Spell Card is on the field, send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This card gains 500 ATK until the end of this turn.

160006035.name: Gate Gargoyle
160006035.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 monster from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Increase the Level of 1 face-up monster on your field by 1 until the end of this turn.

160006036.name: Vietor the Prevailing Wind
160006036.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Choose 1 face-up WIND Attribute monster on your field. If it attacks a Defense Position monster this turn, inflict piercing battle damage (if the ATK of the attacking monster exceeds the DEF of the attack target, inflict the difference).

160006037.name: Bladesaurus
160006037.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This card gains 200 ATK until the end of this turn, then you can add up to 1 each of "Jurassic World" and "Wasteland" from your Graveyard to your hand.

160006038.name: Arzareth the Sweeping Wind
160006038.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 2 cards from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 Spell/Trap Card on your opponent's field.

160006039.name: Road Magic - Uplifter
160006039.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have a face-up Level 7 or higher Spellcaster Type monster on your field, send 1 LIGHT monster from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up monster on your field gains ATK equal to [the ATK of the face-up Level 8 or lower monster on your opponent's field with the lowest ATK] until the end of this turn.

160006040.name: Hypernova
160006040.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have 2 face-up Level 7 non-LIGHT Dragon Type monsters on your field.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 LIGHT Dragon Type monster from your Graveyard to your field face-up.

160006041.name: JAM:P Set!
160006041.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Place 1 Level 2 or lower Psychic Type Normal Monster from your Graveyard on top of the Deck.
[EFFECT]
Place 1 face-up Level 8 or lower monster from your opponent's field on top of the Deck. Then, if you placed "CAN:D" on top of the Deck by this effect's requirement, you can shuffle up to 2 monsters from your opponent's Graveyard into the Deck.

160006042.name: Ruler's Current
160006042.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 Warrior Type monster from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up Warrior Type monster with 2000 or more DEF on your field gains ATK equal to [its original DEF] until the end of this turn.

160006043.name: Against Buster
160006043.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Make 1 face-up WIND Attribute monster with 2000 or more ATK on your field lose 500 ATK until the end of this turn. Then, you can destroy 1 Spell/Trap Card on your opponent's field.

160006044.name: Storm Sonic
160006044.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have 2 or more face-up WIND Attribute monsters on your field.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up monster on your opponent's field loses 600 ATK/DEF until the end of this turn. Then, if you have "Cyber-Tech Alligator"‎ face-up on your field, you can destroy 1 card on your opponent's field.

160006045.name: Following World
160006045.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
While this card is face-up in the Field Zone, all face-up WIND Normal Monsters on the field gain 500 ATK.

160006046.name: Business Card Barrage
160006046.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have a face-up "Worker Warrior - Sinister CEO" on your field.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 face-up Level 7 or lower monster on your opponent's field. Then, if you destroyed a monster by this effect, you can Special Summon 1 Level 5 or lower Machine Type monster from your Graveyard to your field face-up.

160006047.name: Nutrient Zero
160006047.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Gain LP equal to [the Level of 1 face-up Normal Monster on your field] x 100.

160006048.name: Best Bite
160006048.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have a face-up Level 7 or higher Beast Type monster on your field.
[EFFECT]
Send the top 4 cards of your Deck to the Graveyard. Then, if 4 FIRE Beast Type monsters were sent to the Graveyard by this effect, 1 face-up monster on the field gains 2900 ATK until the end of this turn.

160006049.name: B・B・Q
160006049.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Shuffle 1 Beast Type monster from your Graveyard into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
All face-up FIRE monsters on the field gain ATK equal to [the number of face-up FIRE monsters on the field] x 100 until the end of this turn.

160006050.name: Wild Kitchen
160006050.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Activate this card if you have 3 face-up FIRE monsters on your field.
[EFFECT]
While this card is face-up in the Field Zone, all face-up FIRE monsters on the field gain 300 ATK.

160006051.name: Beast Battlefield Barrier
160006051.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
While this card is face-up in the Field Zone, all face-up monsters on the field lose 200 ATK, also all face-up Beast Type Normal Monsters on the field gain 400 DEF.

160006052.name: Dekorelic Dessert
160006052.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Shuffle 4 Pyro Type monsters from your Graveyard into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
All face-up EARTH Pyro Type monsters on your field gain 800 ATK until the end of this turn, then gain 800 LP.

160006053.name: Talismanic Seal Array
160006053.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Shuffle 4 monsters from your Graveyard into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up monster on your opponent's field loses ATK equal to [its Level] x 200 until the end of this turn.

160006054.name: Barrage of Steel
160006054.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have a face-up Machine Type monster on your field.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 Spell/Trap Card on your opponent's field.

160006055.name: Rage of the Beasts
160006055.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have 2 or more face-up Beast and/or Beast-Warrior Type monsters on your field.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 Spell/Trap Card on your opponent's field. Then, if you destroyed a Spell/Trap Card by this effect, you can shuffle 1 Field Spell Card from your Graveyard into the Deck.

160006056.name: Berserker Colosseum
160006056.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Activate this card by sending the top 2 cards of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
While this card is face-up in the Field Zone, all face-up monsters on the field gain 100 ATK.

160006057.name: Mismatched Rivalry
160006057.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent Normal Summons a Level 5 or higher monster.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Level 5 or lower Normal Monster from your Graveyard to your field in face-up Attack Position.

160006058.name: 7 Chance
160006058.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When an opponent's Level 7 or higher monster declares an attack.
[EFFECT]
Draw 3 cards and show them. Then, if there are 2 or more Level 7 monsters among them, gain LP equal to [the number of those Level 7 monsters] x 1500.

160006059.name: Psychicounter
160006059.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your Psychic Type monster is destroyed by an opponent's attack.
[EFFECT]
Inflict 1000 damage to your opponent.

160006060.name: Dark Ruler Battle Slash
160006060.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When an opponent's monster declares an attack on your face-up Warrior Type monster.
[EFFECT]
The attacking monster loses 400 ATK until the end of this turn. Then, if you have a face-up Level 8 or higher Warrior Type monster on your field, you can destroy 1 Spell/Trap Card on your opponent's field.

160006061.name: Covering Barrage
160006061.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When an opponent's monster declares an attack targeting your face-up WIND Attribute monster, shuffle 1 WIND Attribute Normal Monster from your Graveyard into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
The attacking monster loses 1000 ATK until the end of this turn.

160006062.name: Salary Slash
160006062.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When an opponent's Level 8 or lower monster declares an attack on your face-up monster, pay 600 LP.
[EFFECT]
The attacking monster loses 400 ATK until the end of this turn. Monsters cannot be destroyed by that battle.

160006063.name: Battle Demotion
160006063.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When an opponent's monster declares an attack on your face-up Machine Type monster, pay 600 LP.
[EFFECT]
Change 1 Attack Position monster on your opponent's field to face-up Defense Position.

160006064.name: Forever Freeze
160006064.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent Normal Summons a monster with 2500 or more ATK, send 1 monster on your field to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Place that Normal Summoned monster on the bottom of the Deck.

160006065.name: Scaredy Cats
160006065.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent Normal or Special Summons a monster face-up and you have a face-up Beast Type monster on your field.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up monster on your opponent's field loses 1000 ATK until the end of this turn, then you can Special Summon 1 Level 1 Beast Type Normal Monster from your Graveyard to your field face-up.

160007000.name: Levia-Dragon - Daedalus (Rush)
160007000.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 face-up "Umi" from your field to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Destroy all other cards on the field.

160007001.name: Needlkyrie the Celestial Seamstress
160007001.description: A servant of the gods who stitches and sews the way forward. She can illuminate the darkness.

160007002.name: Takriminos (Rush)
160007002.description: A member of a race of sea serpents that freely travels through the sea.

160007003.name: Dolphin King Iruqua
160007003.description: A dolphin that has braved the stormy seas and hardships of the world, throwing itself headfirst into learning the ways of royalty.

160007004.name: Gagaga Outfielder
160007004.description: An enchanting baseball warrior overflowing with guts who excels at defense and unexpected batting. Known as the Magician of the Fence, he's the type who stays in your memory for things besides his records.

160007005.name: Achacha Catcher
160007005.description: An enchanting baseball warrior with a clever lead and throws the ball like an arrow. He is called the keystone of the team, and is the type with a blazing playstyle who helps lead the way for his teammates.

160007006.name: Zubaba Batter
160007006.description: An enchanting baseball warrior whose batting hits as hard as a punch. He is also called the squad captain, and he's the type to give it his all aggressively from the first pitch.

160007007.name: ExPress Train
160007007.description: A train that uses news tips as fuel and runs on the rails of getting scoops. Its fact-gathering and writing are very streamlined.

160007008.name: Flavor Inspector
160007008.description: A pro taste tester who is experienced in the ways of the world, knowing its bitterness and sweetness. She does not judge dishes, except by the quality of their flavor.

160007009.name: Cross Promotion the Elite Noodle Ninja
160007009.description: The head of the Noodle Ninja Corps who have advanced Noodles, overcoming the odds, no matter how noodly things get. He'll gladly speak to people who know nothing of noodles, but he'll make sure neither his location nor his noodles are ever exposed in the process.

160007010.name: Unidentified Mysterious Urchin
160007010.description: A creature that appears everywhere throughout the ocean. Despite massive overfishing, its population doesn't appear to be shrinking.

160007011.name: Necroman the Third
160007011.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If this card was Normal Summoned this turn and your opponent has a face-up Level 7 or higher monster on their field.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Level 3 Normal Monster from your Graveyard to your field face-up.

160007012.name: Daybreak Warrior
160007012.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have a face-up Level 7 Warrior Type monster on your field.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Level 7 Warrior Type monster from your hand to your field face-up.

160007013.name: Porcupine Dragon
160007013.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Pay 500 LP.
[EFFECT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard, then you can add 1 "Mountain" from your Graveyard to your hand.

160007014.name: Psypickupper
160007014.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During your Main Phase in which this card was Normal or Special Summoned, send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This card loses 800 ATK until the end of this turn, then you can gain 800 LP.

160007015.name: Mezame the Ringing Alarm
160007015.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If this card was Normal Summoned this turn and your opponent has a face-up monster with 2500 or more ATK on their field.
[EFFECT]
Add 1 Level 7 or higher Warrior Type monster from your Graveyard to your hand. This turn, you cannot attack with monsters with 1900 or less DEF.

160007016.name: Piercing Samurai
160007016.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have 3 face-up monsters on your field, send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up Warrior Type monster on your field inflicts piercing battle damage this turn (if the ATK of the attacking monster exceeds the DEF of the attack target, inflict the difference).

160007017.name: Kimeluna the Dark Shifter
160007017.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Change the battle positions of up to 2 monsters on your opponent's field (Attack Position becomes face-up Defense Position, Defense Position becomes face-up Attack Position). Then, if you changed a battle position by this effect, you can change the battle position of 1 face-up monster on your field.

160007018.name: Royal Rebel's Break
160007018.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Your opponent has a face-up Level 8 or higher monster on their field.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Level 5 or higher Fiend Type Normal Monster from your hand to your field in face-up Defense Position. Increase this card's Level by 5 until the end of this turn.

160007019.name: Viscom Nanotron
160007019.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
The only monsters in your Graveyard are 3 Cyberse Type monsters.
[EFFECT]
Add all Cyberse Type monsters from your Graveyard to your hand, then place this card from your field on the bottom of the Deck.

160007020.name: Constructor Sky Wyrm Gantry Dragon
160007020.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
A face-up Field Spell is on the field.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 "Constructor Wyrm Buildragon" from your Graveyard to your field face-up. This turn, you cannot attack with non-Wyrm Type monsters.

160007021.name: Light Dolphin
160007021.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have a face-up "Umi" or "Big Umi" and a face-up Fish, Sea Serpent, Thunder, or Aqua Type Normal Monster on your field.
[EFFECT]
Draw 1 card.

160007022.name: Sea Star Trooper
160007022.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Shuffle 1 monster from your opponent's Graveyard into the Deck. Then, if you have "Umi" or "Big Umi" face-up on your field, you can send the top 2 cards of your Deck to the Graveyard.

160007023.name: Kataomoiruka
160007023.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 "Umi" or "Big Umi" from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Draw 1 card.

160007024.name: Head Bad Cachalot
160007024.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up monster on your opponent's field loses 500 ATK until the end of this turn. Then, if you have "Umi" or "Big Umi" face-up on your field, inflict 500 damage to your opponent.

160007025.name: Dododo Second
160007025.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If a face-up "Feverous Spirit Stadium" is on the field, pay 500 LP.
[EFFECT]
This turn, if you would Tribute Summon a FIRE monster in Attack Position, you can treat this face-up card as 2 Tributes.

160007026.name: Gogogo Umpire
160007026.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Shuffle 1 "Feverous Spirit Stadium" from your Graveyard into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 FIRE Normal Monster with 400 DEF from your Graveyard to your field face-up. This turn, you cannot attack with non-FIRE monsters.

160007027.name: Player #99: Grand Slam Dragon
160007027.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Shuffle 3 FIRE monsters from your Graveyard into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 "Player #39: Home Run Hitter" from your Graveyard to your field face-up, then this card gains 2000 ATK until the end of this turn.

160007028.name: Player #39: Home Run Hitter
160007028.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If a face-up "Feverous Spirit Stadium" is on the field, send 2 face-up Level 4 FIRE monsters from your field to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This card gains 2500 ATK until the end of this turn. This turn, you can only attack with this card.

160007029.name: Reporter Raccoon
160007029.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send this face-up card from your field to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 "Printing Presser" from your Graveyard to your field in face-up Defense Position. Then, you can add 1 "Scoop Scooter" or 1 "Soul of a Reporter" from your Graveyard to your hand.

160007030.name: Clean Machine Newsweeper
160007030.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Shuffle 1 EARTH Machine Type monster from your Graveyard into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
Send the top 2 cards of your Deck to the Graveyard. Then, if there is an EARTH Machine Type monster among them, you can add 1 Machine Type Normal Monster from your Graveyard to your hand.

160007031.name: Sea Dragon Kleindros
160007031.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If your opponent has a monster on their field, place 1 "Sea Dragon King Granganus" or 1 "Grand Extreme" from your Graveyard on the bottom of the Deck.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Fish or Sea Serpent Type monster from your hand face-up to your field. This turn, you can only attack with WATER Attribute monsters.

160007032.name: Sea Dragon Knight
160007032.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Shuffle 2 monsters from your Graveyard into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
Look at 1 face-down Spell/Trap Card on your opponent's field. Then, if your opponent has a card with the same name as that card in their Graveyard, you can destroy it.

160007033.name: Dosodon
160007033.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 2 cards from your hand to the Graveyard, including at least 1 Normal Monster.
[EFFECT]
Draw 1 card.

160007034.name: Raidacross Ash, Hero of Chaos
160007034.description:
"Raidacross, Hero of the Dawn" + "Dark Sorcerer"

[REQUIREMENT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[MULTI-CHOICE EFFECT]
● This card gains ATK equal to [the number of monsters on the field] x 300 until the end of this turn.
● Look at all face-down Spell/Trap Cards on your opponent's field, and destroy 1 of them.

160007035.name: CAN:D LIVE
160007035.description:
"CAN:D" + "Psypickupper"

[REQUIREMENT]
Your opponent has a monster on their field.
[MULTI-CHOICE EFFECT]
● Take 2000 damage, then you can make all face-up monsters currently on your opponent's field lose 3000 ATK until the end of this turn.
● Gain 1000 LP, then you can Special Summon 1 Level 7 or higher Psychic Type monster from your Graveyard to your field face-up.

160007036.name: Yamiterasu the Divine Ruler
160007036.description:
"Yamiruler the Dark Delayer" + "Needlkyrie the Celestial Seamstress"

[REQUIREMENT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[MULTI-CHOICE EFFECT]
● Until the end of your opponent's next turn, while this card is face-up, it gains 500 ATK, also neither player can Special Summon Level 9 or lower monsters in face-up Attack Position.
● Change the battle position of 1 monster on the field.

160007037.name: Newsflash the Journalistic Juggernaut
160007037.description:
"Printing Presser" + "Scoop Scooter"

[REQUIREMENT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Your opponent excavates the top 7 cards of their Deck. Your opponent places the excavated cards on the top of their Deck in any order. You can make all face-up monsters on your opponent's field lose ATK equal to [the number of excavated monsters] x 500 until the end of this turn.

160007038.name: Meat Spice the Special Noodle Ninja
160007038.description:
"Extra Spice the Elite Noodle Ninja" + "Flavor Inspector"

[REQUIREMENT]
During your Main Phase that you Special Summoned this card.
[EFFECT]
