160021044.name: Harpie Lady 3 & 1
160021044.description:
"Harpie Lady 3" + 1 Level 4 or lower Winged Beast Type monster
You can Summon this card by Contact Fusion.

[REQUIREMENT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This turn, this card's name becomes "Harpie Lady". During your opponent's next turn, your opponent can only declare up to 2 attacks.

160021045.name: Super Cervical Dragon Elasmortar
160021045.description:
2 Level 4 or lower Dinosaur Type monsters
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[CONTINUOUS EFFECT]
This card cannot be destroyed by card effects. If you have a non-Effect Dinosaur Type Fusion Monster in your Graveyard, this card gains 1200 ATK, and it inflicts piercing battle damage.

160021046.name: Plasmatic Model Rising Lenoir
160021046.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[CONTINUOUS EFFECT]
During your turn, this card gains ATK equal to [its Level] x 200.

160021047.name: Plasmatic Model Rising Lystella
160021047.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During your Main Phase that you Special Summoned this card, shuffle 2 monsters from your Graveyard into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 face-down card on your opponent's field.

160021048.name: Plasmatic Model Rising Blau
160021048.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[CONTINUOUS EFFECT]
Face-down Spell/Trap Cards on your field cannot be destroyed by your opponent's card effects.

160021049.name: Legend Lineage Saber
160021049.description:
This card is treated as a Legend Card while in the Graveyard.
[REQUIREMENT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This card gains 500 ATK until the end of this turn. Then, if you have 3 or more Level 7 monsters with 300 DEF in your Graveyard, you can Special Summon 1 Level 7 monster with 300 DEF from your Graveyard face-up to your field.

160021050.name: Magical Sevens Fusion
160021050.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Fusion Summon a DARK Attribute Spellcaster Type monster with 2100 or less DEF by sending Spellcaster Type monsters from your hand and/or field to the Graveyard as material. This turn, you can only attack with Spellcaster Type monsters.

160021051.name: Strike Tamabowling
160021051.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Choose 1 face-up "Tamabot" on your field and 1 face-up monster with 100 or more ATK on your opponent's field. This turn, your monster gains ATK equal to [that opponent's monster's ATK], and it inflicts piercing battle damage.

160021052.name: Tamalauncher
160021052.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 face-up EARTH Attribute Machine Type monster from your field to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Draw 1 card. Then, if you sent a Level 1 monster with 200 ATK/0 DEF to the Graveyard to meet the requirement, you can draw 1 additional card.

160021053.name: Tama Bond
160021053.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have a face-up EARTH Attribute monster on your field.
[EFFECT]
Fusion Summon a Dragon or Machine Type monster by sending face-up monsters from your field to the Graveyard as material. That monster gains 200 ATK. If a Level 7 EARTH Attribute Machine Type monster is used as material by this effect, its name can be treated as "Blue-Fang Burst Dragon" or "Red-Boot Boost Dragon".

160021054.name: True Shadow Flower Clone
160021054.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have a face-up Level 7 EARTH Attribute Plant Type monster on your field, place 2 cards from your hand on the bottom of the Deck in any order.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon up to 2 Level 7 EARTH Attribute Plant Type monsters from your Graveyard face-up to your field.

160021055.name: Plasmatic Model Open
160021055.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Excavate the top 4 cards of your Deck. You can add 1 excavated Level 4 or lower Thunder Type monster with 800 DEF or 1 "Plasmatic Model Maintenance" to your hand. Place the remaining cards on the bottom of the Deck in any order.

160021056.name: Plasmatic Model Maintenance
160021056.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Equip to 1 face-up LIGHT Attribute Thunder Type monster on your field.
[EFFECT]
The equipped monster gains 500 ATK, and its Level increases by 4. If the equipped monster is a Ritual Monster, it inflicts piercing battle damage.

160021057.name: Plasmatic Model Docking
160021057.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Ritual Summon "Plasmatic Model Rising Lenoir" by sending face-up Thunder Type monsters from your field to the Graveyard whose total Levels equal 8 or more as material (you cannot use more monsters than necessary as material). This turn, you can only attack with Thunder Type monsters.

160021058.name: Plasmatic Model Play
160021058.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Ritual Summon "Plasmatic Model Rising Lystella" or "Plasmatic Model Rising Blau" by sending face-up Thunder Type monsters from your field to the Graveyard whose total Levels equal 8 or more as material (you cannot use more monsters than necessary as material). This turn, you can only attack with Thunder Type monsters.

160021059.name: Legend Advent
160021059.description:
This card is treated as a Legend Card while in the hand or Graveyard.
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Ritual Summon "Legend Lineage Saber" by sending face-up monsters from your field to the Graveyard whose total Levels equal 10 or more as material (you cannot use more monsters than necessary as material).

160021060.name: Triggered Lightning
160021060.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send the top 2 cards of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Choose 1 face-up Effect Monster on your field. This turn, that monster gains 300 ATK and inflicts piercing battle damage. If neither player has cards in their hand, you can Special Summon 1 "Thunder Cavalry Triggerdrago" from your Graveyard face-up to your field.

160021061.name: Medea's Secret Remedy
160021061.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have a Level 9 EARTH Attribute Spellcaster Type monster in your Graveyard, send 2 monsters from your field to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Level 9 EARTH Attribute Spellcaster Type monster from your Graveyard face-up to your field.

160021062.name: Flash Memory Fusion
160021062.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When a monster(s) on your field is destroyed by an opponent's attack or their card effect.
[EFFECT]
Fusion Summon a monster that lists "Blue-Fang Burst Dragon" or "Red-Boot Boost Dragon" as material by shuffling monsters from your Graveyard into the Deck as material. Then, if you activated this card during your turn, your opponent can Special Summon 1 monster from their Graveyard to their field in face-up Attack Position.

160021063.name: Tamatamabangborn
160021063.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When a monster on your field is destroyed by an opponent's attack or their card effect.
[EFFECT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard. Then, you can Special Summon up to 3 "Tamabot" from your Graveyard face-up to your field.

160021064.name: Shadow Flower Bedazzlement
160021064.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent Normal Summons a monster, place 1 EARTH Attribute Plant Type monster from your Graveyard on the bottom of the Deck.
[EFFECT]
Change that Normal Summoned monster to face-down Defense Position. Then, you can Special Summon 1 Plant Type monster with 1000 DEF from your Graveyard face-up to your field.

160021065.name: The Eye of Timaeus (Rush)
160021065.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During a turn you have not activated "The Eye of Timaeus".
[EFFECT]
Declare either "Dark Magician" or "Dark Magician Girl", and Fusion Summon a monster that lists that name as material by sending only 1 face-up monster with the declared name from your field to the Graveyard as material.

160021066.name: Dark Renewal (Rush)
160021066.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent Normal or Special Summons a Level 8 or lower monster face-up, send 1 face-up Spellcaster Type monster from your field to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 of those Normal or Special Summoned monsters. Then, you can Special Summon 1 Level 7 or lower DARK Attribute Spellcaster Type monster from your Graveyard face-up to your field.

160021068.name: Sworn Supporter of the Celestial Saint
160021068.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During your Main Phase that you Normal or Special Summoned this card, pay 500 LP.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 monster from your Graveyard face-up to your field. This turn, you cannot activate the effect of "Sworn Supporter of the Celestial Saint".

160021121.name: Plasmatic Model Lenoir
160021121.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During the turn you Normal Summoned this card, send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Increase this card's Level by 4 until the end of this turn. Then, if you have not drawn a card during this Main Phase, you can draw 1 card.

160021122.name: Plasmatic Model Lystella
160021122.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 other monster from your field to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 Spell/Trap Card on your opponent's field. This turn, you can only attack with Thunder Type monsters.

160021126.name: Dedicated Protorion
160021126.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During your Main Phase that you Normal or Special Summoned this card.
[EFFECT]
Send the top 2 cards of your Deck to the Graveyard. Then, you can Set 1 Ritual Spell Card from your Graveyard to your Spell & Trap Zone.

160021128.name: Rurigra the Eternal
160021128.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During the turn you Normal Summoned this card.
[EFFECT]
Place 1 card from your opponent's Graveyard on the bottom of the Deck. Then, excavate the top 4 cards of your Deck. You can add 1 excavated Level 9 EARTH Attribute Spellcaster Type monster to your hand. Place the other cards on the bottom of your Deck in any order.

160021140.name: Meika Etraynze the Shadow Flower Fiery Flower Beauty
160021140.description:
"Etraynze the Shadow Flower Ninja" + "Himawari the Shadow Flower Eraser"
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[CONTINUOUS EFFECT]
Face-up monsters on your field gain 500 ATK and cannot be destroyed by your opponent's card effects.

160021168.name: Sworn Supporter of the Celestial Saint
160021168.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During your Main Phase that you Normal or Special Summoned this card, pay 500 LP.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 monster from your Graveyard face-up to your field. This turn, you cannot activate the effect of "Sworn Supporter of the Celestial Saint".

160201001.name: Kimeruler the Dark Raider
160201001.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If your opponent has no Attack Position monsters on their field during the turn you Normal Summoned this card, send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This turn, this card can attack directly, also you can only attack with Warrior Type monsters.

160201002.name: Umegumi the Ruler's Squad
160201002.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If a face-up Defense Position monster is on the field, send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up monster on your opponent's field loses 500 ATK/DEF until the end of this turn.

160201003.name: Yurushima Sage
160201003.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Change this Attack Position card to face-up Defense Position.
[EFFECT]
Change 1 Attack Position monster on your opponent's field to face-up Defense Position, and if you do, it loses 600 DEF until the end of this turn.

160201004.name: Yurushima Warrior
160201004.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Shuffle 1 monster with 0 ATK from your Graveyard into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
Choose 1 face-up Warrior Type monster on your field. Your opponent cannot activate Trap Cards when it declares an attack this turn.

160201005.name: Blue Falcon Tengu
160201005.description: A ruthless tengu who leaves opponents stunned by attacking without mercy.

160201006.name: Yurushima the Hermit
160201006.description: A living ball of desires, he criticizes others, but not himself. He's that kind of hermit.

160201007.name: Masaki the Legendary Samurai
160201007.description: This legendary samurai is a veteran of over a hundred battles.

160201008.name: Crying Moon Rabbit
160201008.description: The days and months flowed by. Each day was full. Those really were the good old days.

160201009.name: Shield & Sword (Rush)
160201009.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Switch the original ATK and DEF of all face-up monsters on the field until the end of this turn.

160201010.name: Bonded Bowing
160201010.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Change 1 Attack Position Level 7 or higher Warrior Type monster on your field to face-up Defense Position.
[EFFECT]
Draw 1 card.

160201011.name: Block Attack (Rush)
160201011.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Change 1 Attack Position monster on your opponent's field to face-up Defense Position.

160201012.name: Powerful Pierce!!
160201012.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Choose 2 face-up monsters on your field with the same Level as each other. If those monsters attack a Defense Position monster this turn, inflict piercing battle damage (if the ATK of the attacking monster exceeds the DEF of the attack target, inflict the difference).

160201013.name: Scroll of Salutation
160201013.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent Normal Summons a monster while you have 2 or more face-up Level 5 or higher monsters on your field.
[EFFECT]
Return 1 monster from your field to the owner's hand, also you can change all Attack Position monsters on your field to face-up Defense Position.

160201014.name: Hermit's Soul
160201014.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When an opponent's monster declares an attack targeting your face-up monster with 0 ATK.
[EFFECT]
Change the attacking monster to face-up Defense Position. If you do, you can Special Summon 1 Normal Monster with 0 ATK from your Graveyard face-up to your field.

160201015.name: Royal Rebel's Invasion
160201015.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During the turn you Normal Summoned this card by Tributing 2 Level 5 or higher monsters.
[EFFECT]
Destroy all face-up Level 4 or lower monsters on your opponent's field.

160201016.name: Royal Rebel's Growl
160201016.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During the turn you Normal Summoned this card by Tributing a Level 5 or higher monster, send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up Level 8 or lower monster on your opponent's field loses ATK/DEF equal to [its Level] x 200 until the end of this turn.

160201017.name: Royal Rebel's Rocker
160201017.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During the turn you Normal Summoned this card.
[EFFECT]
Add 1 Level 6 or higher Fiend Type monster from your Graveyard to your hand. You cannot attack directly this turn.

160201018.name: Royal Rebel's Shout
160201018.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If your opponent has a face-up Level 7 or higher monster on their field, send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Send up to 2 random cards from your opponent's hand to the Graveyard.

160201019.name: Palace Gargoyle
160201019.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Increase this card's Level by 1 until the end of this turn.

160201020.name: Followl of the Dark Wisdom
160201020.description: A researcher of the nature of darkness. He serves a king who seeks to conquer the continent, but his true aims are unknown.

160201021.name: Garmr the Lone Wolf
160201021.description: A beast that has refused divine protection, exchanging tranquility for freedom.

160201022.name: Babysitter Goat
160201022.description: A playmate for children of the underworld. Though it is a hard worker, it eats any paper it sees. As its ward grows into an adult, its magical power also grows.

160201023.name: Royal Rebel's Fanatic
160201023.description: A girl who has trouble making eye contact when talking with others. She seeks friends and true love.

160201024.name: King's Reward
160201024.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Shuffle 1 Level 1 Fiend Type Normal Monster from your Graveyard into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 face-up Level 6 or lower monster on your opponent's field. If you do, your opponent draws 1 card. You cannot attack directly this turn.

160201025.name: Genie's Fire Breath
160201025.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have a face-up Fiend Type monster on your field.
[EFFECT]
Return 1 Spell/Trap Card from your opponent's field to the owner's hand.

160201026.name: King's Majesty
160201026.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When an opponent's monster declares an attack, shuffle 1 Level 1 Fiend Type Normal Monster from your Graveyard into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
Negate the attack.

160201027.name: Rebel's Scream
160201027.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent Normal Summons a monster, send 2 Fiend Type monsters from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Destroy all face-up Level 8 or lower monsters on the field.

160201028.name: Folder Blitz the Infinite Dream
160201028.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Your opponent's LP are at least 2000 higher than yours.
[EFFECT]
Inflict 1500 damage to the opponent.

160201029.name: Berry Bassist
160201029.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have a face-up Psychic Type monster other than this card on your field, pay 500 LP.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Level 2 Psychic Type Normal Monster from your Graveyard face-up to your field.

160201030.name: Telepathic Agent
160201030.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If your opponent's LP are at least 1000 higher than yours, shuffle 1 Psychic Type monster from your Graveyard into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
This card can attack directly this turn.

160201031.name: Amusi Performer
160201031.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Pay 800 LP.
[EFFECT]
Inflict 300 damage to your opponent.

160201032.name: Psy Stage Bouncer
160201032.description: The psychic menace has been growing in recent years, and a crack team of bodyguards has been entrusted to protect Psychic Diva, the key to solving it all.

160201033.name: Concert Costume Creator
160201033.description: A designer that uses her psychic talents to make costumes for shows. She is stubborn and won't accept jobs from artists she doesn't like.

160201034.name: Keytar Kid
160201034.description: The youngest member of the band, she's often teased by Romic n' Roller, but everyone recognizes her talents. She dreams of the day she'll play on stage with her bandmates as a quintet.

160201035.name: Howlingbird
160201035.description: A bird that constantly emits sound as it flies with the wind. It is said the noise its wings make reflects the heart of the listener. To some it sounds like a beautiful song, but to others it's an ominous drone.

160201036.name: Elepsychic Amp Up
160201036.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Choose up to 2 face-up Level 2 or lower Psychic Type Normal Monsters on your field, and gain LP equal to [the total ATK of the chosen monsters].

160201037.name: Psychic Divergence
160201037.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have a face-up Psychic Type monster on your field, pay 500 LP.
[EFFECT]
Place 1 Spell/Trap Card from your opponent's field on top of the owner's Deck.

160201038.name: Climax Finale
160201038.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Pay LP equal to [the number of Psychic Type monsters in your Graveyard] x 100.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up Psychic Type monster on your field gains ATK equal to [the number of Psychic Type monsters in your Graveyard] x 100 until the end of this turn.

160201039.name: Psychic Introduction
160201039.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent Normal Summons a monster.
[EFFECT]
Gain LP equal to [the number of face-up Psychic Type monsters on your field] x 500.

160201040.name: Severing Psychic Wall
160201040.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When an opponent's monster declares an attack targeting your face-up Psychic Type monster, shuffle 1 Psychic Type monster from your Graveyard into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
The attack target gains 500 ATK until the end of this turn.

160202001.name: Supreme Machine Magnum Overlord [L]
160202001.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Maximum Mode: If your LP are lower than your opponent's, send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This card gains ATK equal to [the difference between your LP and your opponent's LP] until the end of this turn.

160202002.name: Supreme Machine Magnum Overlord
160202002.description:
MAXIMUM ATK = 3500
You can Maximum Summon this card together with "Supreme Machine Magnum Overlord [L]" and "Supreme Machine Magnum Overlord [R]".

[REQUIREMENT]
Maximum Mode
[CONTINUOUS EFFECT]
This card cannot be destroyed by your opponent's Trap Card effects.

160202003.name: Supreme Machine Magnum Overlord [R]
160202003.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Maximum Mode: Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This card gains ATK equal to [the Level of 1 face-up monster on your opponent's field] x 200 until the end of this turn.

160202004.name: Kuribot
160202004.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have no other monsters on your field, pay 500 LP.
[EFFECT]
Add 1 "Kuribot" from your Graveyard to your hand.

160202005.name: Kuribotriple
160202005.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Shuffle 3 "Kuribot" from your Graveyard into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
Draw 2 cards.

160202006.name: Silent Learning
160202006.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have Level 5 or higher monsters of at least 3 different Types in your Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Look at 1 face-down card in your opponent's Spell & Trap Zone then return it to its original position. If it was a Trap Card, place 1 Level 5 or higher monster from your Graveyard on the bottom of your Deck and draw 1 card.

160202007.name: Cranked to Ten!!
160202007.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 monster from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Choose 1 face-up monster on your field. This turn, it gains 400 ATK, and if it attacks a Defense Position monster, inflict piercing battle damage (if the ATK of the attacking monster exceeds the DEF of the attack target, inflict the difference). If the monster's Level is 10, inflict 1000 damage to your opponent.

160202008.name: Magiquartet Shock
160202008.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent Special Summons a monster(s) with 1500 or more ATK face-up, shuffle 4 Normal Monsters from your Graveyard into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 monster on your opponent's field.

160202009.name: Widening Whisper
160202009.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent Sets a monster from their hand.
[EFFECT]
Shuffle up to 5 monsters from the Graveyards into the owner's Decks.

160202010.name: Yggdrago the Sky Emperor [L]
160202010.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Maximum Mode: Send the top 3 cards of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 face-up Level 8 or lower monster on your opponent's field.

160202011.name: Yggdrago the Sky Emperor
160202011.description:
MAXIMUM ATK = 4000
You can Maximum Summon this card together with "Yggdrago the Sky Emperor [L]" and "Yggdrago the Sky Emperor [R]".

[REQUIREMENT]
Maximum Mode
[CONTINUOUS EFFECT]
This card cannot be destroyed by your opponent's Trap Card effects.

160202012.name: Yggdrago the Sky Emperor [R]
160202012.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Maximum Mode: Send the top 3 cards of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Change 1 Defense Position monster on your opponent's field to face-up Attack Position.

160202013.name: Peacock Picotron
160202013.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have no other monsters on your field and have "Femtron" in your Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Send this card from your field to the Graveyard and draw 2 cards. Then, send the top 2 cards of your Deck to the Graveyard.

160202014.name: Femtron
160202014.description: The source of the draconic tree that holds the secret of all providence. When assailed by microcosm and macrocosm, the world will be guided to a new domain.

160202015.name: Attron
160202015.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have no other monsters on your field and have "Femtron" in your Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Send this card from your field to the Graveyard and draw 1 card.

160202016.name: Zeptron
160202016.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have no other monsters on your field and have "Femtron" and "Attron" in your Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Send this card from your field to the Graveyard and draw 2 cards. Then, place 2 cards from your hand on the bottom of your Deck in any order.

160202017.name: Yoctron
160202017.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Place 1 "Femtron", 1 "Attron", and 1 "Zeptron" from your Graveyard on the bottom of your Deck in any order.
[EFFECT]
Send this card from your field to the Graveyard and draw 3 cards. Then, send 3 cards from your hand to the Graveyard.

160202018.name: Pair Production
160202018.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 2 Level 5 or lower Cyberse Type monsters with the same Level from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up monster on your field gains ATK equal to [the Level of 1 of the monsters sent to the Graveyard to meet the requirement] x 400 until the end of this turn.

160202019.name: Trap Hole (Rush)
160202019.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent Normal Summons a monster with 1000 or more ATK.
[EFFECT]
Destroy that monster.

160202020.name: Quantum Hole
160202020.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When a Cyberse Type monster on your field is destroyed in battle by an opponent's attack.
[EFFECT]
Draw 2 cards. Then, place 2 cards from your hand on the bottom of your Deck in any order.

160202021.name: Clean Beret - Colonel Mop
160202021.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Your opponent has a face-up Level 7 or higher monster on their field.
[EFFECT]
Place 1 "Bleach Mortar" from your Graveyard on top of your Deck.

160202022.name: Scrubbing Santa Cloth
160202022.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During your Main Phase that you Normal Summoned or Special Summoned this card.
[EFFECT]
Your opponent draws cards equal to [the number of monsters on their field]. Then, you gain LP equal to [the number of cards they drew by this effect] x 300.

160202023.name: Washsprayer the Cleansketeer
160202023.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You Normal Summoned this card this turn and your opponent has a face-up Level 7 or higher monster on their field.
[EFFECT]
Shuffle 1 "Bleach Mortar" from your Graveyard into the Deck. Then draw 1 card.

160202024.name: Bleach Mortar
160202024.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
1 face-up Level 7 or higher monster on your opponent's field loses 500 ATK until the end of this turn. Inflict 500 damage to your opponent.

160202025.name: Odd-Eyes Twin Tail Cat
160202025.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have "Red-Eyes Black Cat" and "Blue-Eyes White Cat" face-up on your field.
[EFFECT]
Add 1 "Lost Cat" from your Graveyard to your hand.

160202026.name: Red-Eyes Black Cat
160202026.description: A black cat with red eyes. Said to bring bad luck to those around it.

160202027.name: Blue-Eyes White Cat
160202027.description: A white cat with blue eyes. Said to bring good luck if treated well.

160202028.name: Cat's Eye
160202028.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have 3 face-up Beast Type monsters on your field.
[EFFECT]
Your opponent declares 1 card type (Monster, Spell, or Trap) and sends the top card of their Deck to the Graveyard. If it was not the declared card type, all face-up monsters on your field can attack directly this turn.

160202029.name: Lost Cat
160202029.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When an opponent's monster declares an attack.
[EFFECT]
Your opponent declares a card type (Monster, Spell, or Trap) and sends the top card of their Deck to the Graveyard. If it was not the declared card type, negate the attack, and inflict 300 damage to the opponent.

160202030.name: Thunderbeetle Bassdrum
160202030.description:
A gentle but powerful and trustworthy creature that stands in the background.
It sends out its sounds every day with the belief that it will find friends it can resonate with.

160202031.name: Thunderbeetle Highhat
160202031.description:
A multifaceted older brother type.
It sends out its sounds every day with the belief that it will find friends it can resonate with.

160202032.name: Thunderbeetle Snare
160202032.description:
Popular, unique, and always energetic.
It sends out its sounds every day with the belief that it will find friends it can resonate with.

160202033.name: Thunderbeetle Gift
160202033.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have a face-up Level 4 or lower Thunder Type monster on your field.
[EFFECT]
Inflict damage to your opponent equal to [the number of face-up Thunder Type monsters on your field] x 500. Your monsters cannot attack this turn.

160202034.name: Thunderbeetle Storm
160202034.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have 3 face-up Level 4 or lower Thunder Type monsters on your field.
[EFFECT]
Destroy all face-up Level 8 or lower Effect Monsters on your opponent's field. If you destroyed any monster by this effect, you cannot Normal or Special Summon monsters until the end of this turn.

160202035.name: Thunderbeetle Boost
160202035.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When an opponent's Level 8 or lower monster with ATK greater than your LP declares an attack while you have a face-up Thunder Type monster on your field.
[EFFECT]
Gain LP equal to [the ATK of 1 face-up monster on your opponent's field].

160202036.name: Throne of Darkness
160202036.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have 8 or more monsters with 0 ATK in your Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Level 7 or higher monster with 0 ATK from your hand to your field in Attack Position.

160202037.name: Dahut, Dark Ruler of the Chair
160202037.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This card gains ATK equal to [the Level of 1 other face-up monster on your field with 0 ATK] x 500 until the end of this turn.

160202038.name: Scarechair Gear
160202038.description: A mechanical chair that is easy to mass produce. It is not as comfortable to sit in as the organic chairs from before.

160202039.name: Scarechair Bone
160202039.description: One of the earliest organic chairs said to be made by a family of artisans. Has a distinctive feel when sat upon.

160202040.name: Scarechair Saber
160202040.description: A masterpiece organic chair made by a family of artisans at the peak of their craft. Extremely comfortable.

160202041.name: Collapsing Chairs
160202041.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your Attack Position DARK Attribute monster with 0 ATK is destroyed by an opponent's attack.
[EFFECT]
Destroy all Level 8 or lower Attack Position monsters on the field. Then, each player sends cards equal to [the number of monsters destroyed by this effect] from the top of their Deck to the Graveyard.

160202042.name: Cosmic String Noodryad
160202042.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If "Outer Space" is face-up on the field, send 2 Pyro Type monsters from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Destroy all face-up Level 7 or lower monsters on the field.

160202043.name: Galaxy Topping Troll
160202043.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If "Outer Space" is face-up on the field, send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This card gains 600 ATK until the end of this turn.

160202044.name: Cosmoscallion
160202044.description: A maiden who freely drifts around the Milky Way like a shooting star. Countless people make wishes on her, but she dryly states that real dreams are the ones you can fulfill on your own.

160202045.name: Big Bang Egger
160202045.description: Which came first, space or the egg? This girl has an explosive imagination.

160202046.name: Outer Space
160202046.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
While this card is face-up in the Field Zone, face-up Level 4 or lower monsters on the field lose 300 ATK/DEF.

160202047.name: Chashooting Star
160202047.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent Normal Summons or Special Summons a Level 5 or higher monster face-up.
[EFFECT]
Gain LP equal to [the Level of 1 face-up Pyro Type monster on your field] x 200. Then, return it to the owner's hand.

160202048.name: Card Destruction (Rush)
160202048.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Each player with cards in their hand sends their entire hand to the Graveyard, then draws cards equal to [the number of cards each player sent to the Graveyard by this effect].

160202049.name: Shrinker Shrimp
160202049.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send up to 2 face-up Cyberse Type monsters from your field to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up monster on your opponent's field loses ATK equal to [the number of monsters sent to the Graveyard to meet the requirement] x 300 until the end of this turn.

160202050.name: Heavenly Gift
160202050.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Send any number of monsters from your hand to the Graveyard. If [the total Levels of those monsters sent to the Graveyard by this effect] is 10 or higher, you can draw 2 cards.

160203001.name: Supreme Skystream Magnum Overlord [L]
160203001.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Maximum Mode: Shuffle 1 monster from your Graveyard into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
Inflict damage to your opponent equal to [the Level of 1 monster in your Graveyard] x 100, then, if you inflicted damage to your opponent by this effect, you can add that monster to your hand.

160203002.name: Supreme Skystream Magnum Overlord
160203002.description:
MAXIMUM ATK = 3500
Can be Maximum Summoned together with "Supreme Skystream Magnum Overlord [L]" and "Supreme Skystream Magnum Overlord [R]".

[REQUIREMENT]
Maximum Mode: Send this face-up card from your field to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon up to 2 monsters from your hand to your field face-up, then you can destroy 1 Spell/Trap Card on your opponent's field.

160203003.name: Supreme Skystream Magnum Overlord [R]
160203003.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Maximum Mode: Send the top 2 cards of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This card loses 1000 ATK until the end of this turn. This turn, this card cannot attack directly, it can attack all your opponent's monsters once each, also it inflicts piercing battle damage.

160203004.name: Emergency Return
160203004.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When an opponent's monster declares an attack.
[EFFECT]
Return 1 face-up Level 5 or higher monster from your field to the hand. If you returned a monster to the hand by this effect, negate that attack.

160203005.name: Dynamic Dino Dynamix [L]
160203005.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Maximum Mode
[CONTINUOUS EFFECT]
This card cannot be destroyed by battle with Level 7 or lower monsters.

160203006.name: Dynamic Dino Dynamix
160203006.description:
MAXIMUM ATK = 3400
Can be Maximum Summoned together with "Dynamic Dino Dynamix [L]" and "Dynamic Dino Dynamix [R]".

[REQUIREMENT]
Maximum Mode: If your opponent has no face-up Level 9 or higher monsters on their field, send 1 monster from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Destroy up to 2 monsters on your opponent's field.

160203007.name: Dynamic Dino Dynamix [R]
160203007.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Maximum Mode
[CONTINUOUS EFFECT]
This card cannot be destroyed by the effects of your opponent's Trap Cards.

160203008.name: Sneezing Greedizauls
160203008.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If your LP are lower than your opponent's, place 1 card from your hand on the bottom of the Deck.
[EFFECT]
Send the top 2 cards of each player's Deck to the Graveyard, then, if a monster was sent to the Graveyard by this effect, inflict damage to your opponent equal to [the number of monsters sent to the Graveyard by this effect] x 400.

160203009.name: Mech Therizinoraptor
160203009.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 Dinosaur Type monster from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Draw 1 card.

160203010.name: Ritzy King Rex
160203010.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Your opponent has no cards in their hand.
[EFFECT]
Each player draws 1 card, then, if both players drew by this effect, you can Set 1 "Upstart Goblin" from your Graveyard to your Spell & Trap Zone.

160203011.name: Supressaurus Sternptera
160203011.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard, then you can place 1 random card from your opponent's hand on the bottom of the Deck.

160203012.name: Uraby (Rush)
160203012.description: Fast on its feet, this dinosaur rips enemies to shreds with its sharp claws.

160203013.name: Celebrontosaurus
160203013.description: A newly rich Saurus who changed its name from Petite and became absurdly lucky. It used to live in a cave of all things.

160203014.name: Platnidon
160203014.description: A Pteranodon that loves to collect shiny metals. The shell on its head is its favorite.

160203015.name: Jurassic World (Rush)
160203015.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
While this card is face-up in the Field Zone, all face-up Dinosaur Type monsters on the field gain 300 ATK/DEF.

160203016.name: Coevolutionary Miracle
160203016.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 face-up Dinosaur Type monster from your field to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Level 5 or higher Dinosaur Type monster from your hand to your field face-up. The monster Special Summoned by this effect gains ATK equal to [the original Level of the monster sent to the Graveyard by the requirement of this effect] x 100 until the end of this turn.

160203017.name: Dinosaur Crush
160203017.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have a face-up Level 7 or higher Dinosaur Type monster on your field, send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 face-down card on your opponent's field.

160203018.name: Upstart Goblin (Rush)
160203018.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Draw 1 card, then your opponent gains 1000 LP.

160203019.name: Ascending Evolution
160203019.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent Normal Summons a Level 7 or higher monster.
[EFFECT]
This turn, 1 face-up Level 7 or higher Dinosaur Type monster on your field gains 1500 ATK, also it cannot be destroyed by your opponent's card effects.

160203020.name: Dinomic Pressure
160203020.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When an opponent's monster declares an attack, shuffle 3 Dinosaur Type monsters from your Graveyard into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
All face-up monsters on your opponent's field lose 1000 ATK until the end of this turn.

160203021.name: Seedchrotron Brusselun
160203021.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During the turn this card was Normal Summoned.
[EFFECT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard. Then, if a Cyberse Type monster was sent to the Graveyard by this effect, you can add Cyberse Type monsters with 0 DEF from your Graveyard to your hand, up to [the number of face-up monsters on your opponent's field].

160203022.name: Cycliptron
160203022.description: The cornerstone of the dragon tree that houses the providence of creation. As it breaks the absolute limit, it will push to a new unseen territory.

160203023.name: Tribute to The Doomed (Rush)
160203023.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 monster on the field.

160203024.name: Dahut Abyss, Dark Mirror Ruler of the Chair
160203024.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Shuffle any number of monsters with 0 ATK from your Graveyard into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
1 other face-up monster on the field loses ATK equal to [the number of monsters shuffled into the Deck to meet the requirement] x 300 until the end of this turn. This card gains ATK equal to [the number of monsters shuffled into the Deck to meet the requirement] x 300 until the end of this turn.

160203025.name: Scarechair Relaxer
160203025.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 monster with 0 ATK from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Send the top 2 cards of your Deck to the Graveyard. Then, if a Level 8 or lower DARK monster(s) is among the cards sent, add 1 Level 8 or lower DARK monster from your Graveyard to your hand. Your opponent gains LP equal to [that monster's ATK].

160203026.name: Scarechair Scale
160203026.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you control no other monsters, place 2 monsters with 0 ATK from your Graveyard on the bottom of the Deck in any order.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Level 5 or higher monster with 0 ATK from your Graveyard to your field in face-up Attack Position.

160203027.name: Darkness Ri-chair-al
160203027.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have a DARK monster in your Graveyard, send 3 face-up DARK monsters from your field to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 DARK monster from your Graveyard to your field face-up. Then, if you have 3 DARK monsters with the same name in your Graveyard, you can draw 1 card.

160203028.name: Joining Chairs
160203028.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent Normal Summons a monster while you have 3 face-up monsters with 0 ATK on your field.
[EFFECT]
Change up to 2 monsters on your field to face-up Defense Position. This turn, if you have a Defense Position monster on your field, your opponent's monsters can only attack Defense Position monsters.

160203029.name: Constructor Demolisher Wyrm Drake Crush
160203029.description: A Constructor Dragon whose entire body is armed with special tools and equipment. It is said it has enough power to demolish any major location in an instant.

160203030.name: Silvermountain of Blisstopia
160203030.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Activate this card if your opponent has a face-up Level 7 or higher monster on their field.
[EFFECT]
While this card is face-up in the Field Zone, if a player would Tribute Summon a Level 7 or higher Wyrm Type monster in Attack Position, they require only 1 Tribute.

160203031.name: Constructor Art - Buildestruction
160203031.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
All face-up Level 7 or higher Wyrm Type Normal Monsters on your field gain 600 ATK until the end of this turn. Then, you can make all face-up monsters with 3000 or more ATK on your opponent's field lose 1200 ATK until the end of this turn.

160203032.name: Hammer Crush
160203032.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 Spell/Trap Card on your opponent's field.

160203033.name: Constructor Resurrection
160203033.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your Level 7 or higher Wyrm Type monster is destroyed by an opponent's attack.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Level 7 or higher Wyrm Type monster from your Graveyard to your field face-up.

160203034.name: Clubinet the Music Princess
160203034.description: The jack of all trades of the Ensemble Squadron. Her gentle melodies give rise to attacks. When she gets excited, the light on her head lights up.

160203035.name: Horn Knives the Music Princess
160203035.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During the turn this card was Normal Summoned.
[EFFECT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard, then, if a Warrior Type monster was sent to the Graveyard by this effect, you can add 1 Warrior Type Normal Monster from your Graveyard to your hand.

160203036.name: Straight Pierce
160203036.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Shuffle 5 WIND Warrior Type monsters from your Graveyard into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
This turn, 1 face-up Level 7 or 8 monster on your field gains 2000 ATK and inflicts piercing battle damage (if the ATK of the attacking monster exceeds the DEF of the attack target, inflict the difference).

160203037.name: Music Princess's Whirling Wind
160203037.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have a face-up Level 5 or higher WIND Warrior Type monster on your field.
[EFFECT]
Change up to 2 Attack Position monsters on your opponent's field to face-up Defense Position.

160203038.name: Music Princess Art - Triplet
160203038.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent Normal or Special Summons a monster, if they have 3 monsters on their field.
[EFFECT]
All face-up WIND Warrior Type monsters on your field gain 1000 ATK until the end of this turn.

160203039.name: Agariel, the Finest Sushi Fairy
160203039.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 Fairy Type monster from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up monster on your field gains 1000 ATK until the end of this turn.

160203040.name: Dragon Roll the Sushi Fairy
160203040.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have 10 or more cards in your Deck during the turn you Normal Summoned this card, place 1 Fairy Type monster from your Graveyard on the bottom of the Deck.
[EFFECT]
Draw 1 card. This turn, you cannot attack with Level 6 or lower monsters.

160203041.name: Tiger Roll the Sushi Fairy
160203041.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Add up to 2 Level 8 or lower Fairy Type monsters from your Graveyard to your hand. You cannot Normal Summon/Set or Special Summon monsters from the hand for the rest of this turn.

160203042.name: Monkey Roll the Sushi Fairy
160203042.description: A follower of the gods that dine in the Divine Sushi Realm. All of the rice is swept up by their characteristic seaweed and peculiar sweetness.

160203043.name: Spider Roll the Sushi Fairy
160203043.description: A follower of the gods that dine in the Divine Sushi Realm. All of the rice is swept over by their characteristic seaweed and peculiar aroma.

160203044.name: Inside Out Roll
160203044.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have a face-up Level 5 or higher Fairy Type monster on your field.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up monster on your opponent's field loses 500 ATK until the end of this turn, then, if your opponent's LP are at least 2000 higher than yours, that monster loses 1500 more ATK until the end of this turn.

160203045.name: Angel Judge
160203045.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have a face-up Fairy Type monster on your field.
[EFFECT]
Place 1 Spell/Trap Card on your opponent's field on the bottom of the Deck.

160203046.name: Rolled Sticky Save
160203046.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When an opponent's monster declares an attack.
[EFFECT]
1 Attack Position Fairy Type monster on your field cannot be destroyed by battle this turn. Your opponent gains LP equal to [that monster's ATK].

160203047.name: Rolled Hot Arrow
160203047.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent Normal or Special Summons a monster.
[EFFECT]
Inflict 500 damage to your opponent. If you have a face-up Fairy Type monster on your field, you can Special Summon 1 Fairy Type monster from your hand to your field face-up.

160203048.name: Startup Goblin
160203048.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send this face-up card from your field to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Level 6 or lower monster from your hand to your field face-up. The monster Special Summoned by this effect gains 500 ATK until the end of this turn. Then, if you have "Upstart Goblin" in your Graveyard, inflict 500 damage to your opponent.

160203049.name: Heavenly Revelation
160203049.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Send any number of monsters from your field to the Graveyard. Then, if [the total original Levels of the monsters sent to the Graveyard by this effect] are 10 or more, you can Special Summon 1 Level 8 or lower monster from your Graveyard to your field face-up. The monster Special Summoned by this effect gains 300 ATK until the end of this turn.

160203050.name: Turnback Shot
160203050.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent draws for their normal draw in their Draw Phase.
[EFFECT]
Return 1 face-up Level 8 or lower monster on your opponent's field to the hand.

160204001.name: Metarion Ashurastar
160204001.description:
"Imaginary Actor" + "Sword Dancer"

[REQUIREMENT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[MULTI-CHOICE EFFECT]
● Destroy 1 face-down card on your opponent's field.
● 1 face-up Cyborg Type monster on your field gains ATK equal to [the total ATK of all face-up Warrior Type monsters currently on your opponent's field] until the end of this turn.

160204002.name: Metarion Vritrastar
160204002.description:
"Imaginary Actor" + "Serpainter"

[REQUIREMENT]
None
[MULTI-CHOICE EFFECT]
● Change 1 monster on your opponent's field to face-up Attack Position or face-down Defense Position.
● Destroy face-up Dragon Type monsters on your opponent's field, up to [the number of face-up Cyborg Type monsters on your field].

160204003.name: Metarion Eraclestar
160204003.description:
"Imaginary Actor" + "Magic Juggler"

[REQUIREMENT]
Place 1 card from your Graveyard on the bottom of the Deck.
[MULTI-CHOICE EFFECT]
● Shuffle up to 3 monsters from your opponent's Graveyard into the Deck.
● Shuffle up to 2 face-up Spellcaster Type monsters on your opponent's field into the Deck.

160204004.name: Metarion Ladonstar
160204004.description:
"Imaginary Actor" + "Glaciasaurus"

[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[MULTI-CHOICE EFFECT]
● 1 face-up monster on your opponent's field loses 1500 ATK/DEF until the end of this turn.
● All face-up Dinosaur Type monsters currently on your opponent's field lose 2000 ATK/DEF until the end of this turn.

160204005.name: Fire Jester
160204005.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have a face-up Level 5 or higher LIGHT monster on your field, send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up Level 8 or lower monster on your opponent's field loses 500 ATK/DEF until the end of this turn.

160204006.name: Imaginary Actor
160204006.description: A mechanical doll incapable of expressing emotions outside of laughing. It uses the emotions of its audience as energy.

160204007.name: Glaciasaurus
160204007.description: A gentle dinosaur that doesn't like conflict. It's always gracefully watching the audience.

160204008.name: Serpainter
160204008.description: A beautiful dragon that once lived in a clear and pure watering hole. Now it serves as the popular mascot of the circus, adored by the audience.

160204009.name: Sword Dancer
160204009.description: A master swordsman that used to serve a great nation. He controls his flying swords with great precision as the audience watches attentively.

160204010.name: Magic Juggler
160204010.description: A very mysterious man who doesn't spell about his past. He captures the attention of the audience by manipulating his baton almost as if it were magic.

160204011.name: Imaginary Arc Turbo
160204011.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up Level 9 LIGHT monster or 1 face-up LIGHT Normal Monster on your field gains 500 ATK until the end of this turn. Then, if you have "Imaginary Actor" in your Graveyard, that monster gains 1000 more ATK until the end of this turn.

160204012.name: Imaginary Arc Tower
160204012.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Activate this card if you have a LIGHT Normal Monster with 500 DEF in your Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
While this card is face-up in the Field Zone, all face-up non-LIGHT monsters on the field lose 300 ATK, also face-up Level 9 LIGHT monsters on the field cannot be destroyed by Trap effects.

160204013.name: Imaginary Arc Turbulence
160204013.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent Normal or Special Summons a monster, and you have a LIGHT Normal Monster with 500 DEF in your Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Change 1 Attack Position Level 8 or higher LIGHT monster on your field to face-up Defense Position, then you can destroy 1 face-up monster on your opponent's field with the same Type as a Normal Monster in your Graveyard.

160204014.name: Imaginary Arc Turnback
160204014.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your Attack Position LIGHT monster is destroyed by an opponent's attacking monster.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Cyborg Type monster or 1 LIGHT Normal Monster with 500 DEF from your Graveyard to your field face-up.

160204015.name: Sevens Paladin
160204015.description:
"Sevens Road Magician" + "Swordsman of Roadstar"

[REQUIREMENT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[MULTI-CHOICE EFFECT]
● This card gains ATK equal to [the number of different Attributes in the Graveyards] x 400 until the end of this turn.
● Shuffle 1 monster from your Graveyard into the Deck, then draw 1 card.

160204016.name: Whispark Fairy Girl
160204016.description:
"Sparkhearts Girl" + "Whispering Fairy"

[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Shuffle up to 2 monsters from your opponent's Graveyard into the Deck, then you can make all face-up monsters on your opponent's field lose 500 ATK until the end of this turn.

160204017.name: Straynge Cats
160204017.description:
"Straynge Cat" + "Straynge Cat"

[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Spellcaster Type Normal Monster from your Graveyard face-up to your field. Then, if you Special Summoned "Straynge Cat" by this effect, this card gains 1400 ATK until the end of this turn.

160204018.name: Kuribotorero
160204018.description:
"Kuribot" + "Siesta Torero"

[REQUIREMENT]
Pay 500 LP.
[EFFECT]
Return 1 Defense Position monster from your opponent's field to the hand.

160204019.name: Kuribot
160204019.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have no other monsters on your field, pay 500 LP.
[EFFECT]
Add 1 "Kuribot" from your Graveyard to your hand.

160204020.name: Mr. Alchemy
160204020.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have no other monsters on your field, send this face-up card on your field to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]

Then, this turn, this card inflicts piercing battle damage. Then, if "Sevens Road Magician" is in your Graveyard, this turn, this card cannot be destroyed by card effects.

160211063.name: Super Graphagas Vapor Lancer
160211063.description:

[EFFECT]
Send the top 3 cards of your Deck to the Graveyard. Then, your opponent returns as many face-up cards from their field to the owner's hand as possible, up to [the number of FIRE Attribute monsters with different Types sent to the Graveyard by this effect].

160211064.name: Dian Keto the Food Prodigy
160211064.description:

160211065.name: Dian Keto the Cleaning Maiden
160211065.description:

160211067.name: Dicemite Girl Laps
160211067.description:

[EFFECT]

● 7 or 11: Place 1 card from your opponent's field on the bottom of the owner's Deck.
● 2, 3, or 12: Change the battle position of 1 monster on your field.

160211068.name: Dice Key Nel
160211068.description:

160211070.name: Impactor Comet

160213046.name: Crawling Dragon #2 (Rush)

160213047.name: Two-Headed King Rex (Rush)
160213047.description: A powerful monster whose two heads attack as one.

160213048.name: Jurassic Draw
160213048.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 Dinosaur Type monster from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Draw 2 cards. This turn, you can only attack with Dinosaur Type monsters.

160213049.name: Giant Dynamix Impact
160213049.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Shuffle 4 Dinosaur Type monsters from your Graveyard into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 card on your opponent's field. Then, if you have a face-up Level 10 Dinosaur Type monster on your field, you can inflict 1000 damage to your opponent.

160213050.name: Dyna Body Heat
160213050.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Equip this card to 1 face-up Dinosaur Type monster on your field .
[EFFECT]
The equipped monster cannot be destroyed by your opponent's card effects , and it inflicts piercing battle damage. During your opponent's turn, while the equipped monster is face-up on your field, it cannot be returned to the hand, Deck, or Extra Deck by card effects.

160213051.name: Ultra Evolution Miracle
160213051.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent draws a card during their turn.
[EFFECT]
Choose 1 face-up Dinosaur Type monster on your field. This turn, that monster cannot be destroyed by card effects. Then, you can Fusion Summon a Level 9 or lower Dinosaur Type monster by shuffling 2 Dinosaur Type monsters from your Graveyard into the Deck as material.

160213052.name: Oneirophrenia Delirium Silbyx
160213052.description:
2 Level 7-9 Insect Type Effect Monsters
[REQUIREMENT]
During your Main Phase that you Fusion Summoned this card, shuffle 3 non-Level 9 Insect Type monsters from your Graveyard into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
This card gains 500 ATK until the end of this turn. Then, you can shuffle 1 card from your opponent's field into the owner's Deck.

160213053.name: Fleeting Delirium Silbyx
160213053.description:
1 Level 7-9 Insect Type Effect Monster + 1 Insect Type Effect Monster
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[CONTINUOUS EFFECT]
Face-up Insect Type monsters on your field cannot be destroyed by your opponent's card effects. Your opponent cannot use monsters on your field as material for a Fusion Summon.

160213054.name: Delirium Larva
160213054.description:
2 Level 6 or lower Insect Type Effect Monsters
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[CONTINUOUS EFFECT]
Face-up Insect Type monsters on your field gains 800 ATK. During your opponent's turn, Spell/Trap Cards on your field cannot be returned to the hand, Deck, or Extra Deck by card effects.

160213055.name: Delirium Silbyx
160213055.description:
You can Tribute Summon this card in Attack Position by Tributing 1 LIGHT Attribute Insect Type monster.
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Fusion Summon a LIGHT Attribute Insect Type monster by sending monsters from your hand and/or field to the Graveyard as material.

160213056.name: Delirium Calabrone
160213056.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have a LIGHT Attribute Insect Type monster in your Graveyard, send the top 3 cards of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This card gains 500 ATK until the end of this turn. Then, you can add 1 "Delirium Silbyx" from your Graveyard to your hand.

160213057.name: Delirium Mariquita
160213057.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have another face-up LIGHT Attribute Insect Type monster on your field, change this Attack Position card to face-up Defense Position.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up monster on your opponent's field loses 500 ATK/DEF until the end of this turn. Then, you can make 1 face-up monster on your opponent's field become Insect Type until the end of their next turn.

160213058.name: Delirium Shuel
160213058.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have another face-up LIGHT Attribute Insect Type monster on your field, change this Attack Position card to face-up Defense Position.
[EFFECT]
Change the battle position of 1 monster on your opponent's field. Then, you can make 1 face-up monster on your opponent's field become Insect Type until the end of their next turn.

160213059.name: Delirium Drone
160213059.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have another face-up LIGHT Attribute Insect Type monster on your field, change this Attack Position card to face-up Defense Position.
[EFFECT]
Send the top 2 cards of your Deck to the Graveyard. Then, you can make 1 face-up monster on your opponent's field become Insect Type until the end of their next turn.

160213062.name: Pinch Hopper (Rush)
160213062.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send this face-up card from your field to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Insect Type monster from your hand face-up to your field.

160213064.name: Delirium Honeyed Words
160213064.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Send the top 2 cards of your Deck to the Graveyard. Then, you can add to your hand 1 LIGHT Attribute Insect Type monster, "Delirium Embrace", or "Delirium Rebirth" from among the cards sent.

160213065.name: Delirium Embrace
160213065.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Fusion Summon a LIGHT Attribute Insect Type monster by sending 1 face-up monster from your field and 1 face-up Level 9 or lower monster from either field to the Graveyard as material. This turn, you can only attack with Insect Type monsters.

160213067.name: Delirium Rebirth
160213067.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent draws a card during their turn, or when your opponent Normal or Special Summons a monster during their turn, while you have an Insect Type monster in your Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Fusion Summon a LIGHT Attribute Insect Type monster by sending 1 face-up monster from your field and 1 face-up Level 9 or lower monster from either field to the Graveyard as material.

160213068.name: Lair Wire (Rush)
160213068.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent Normal Summons a monster, place 1 Insect Type monster from your Graveyard on the bottom of your Deck.
[EFFECT]
Destroy that Normal Summoned monster.

160213069.name: Pliage the Sacred Shooting Star
160213069.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have not drawn a card during this Main Phase.
[EFFECT]
Add 1 "Star Restart" or "Star of the Beginning" from your Graveyard to your hand. Then, draw 1 card.

160213076.name: Red-Eyes Black Dragon (Rush)
160213076.description: A ferocious dragon with a deadly attack.

160213078.name: Super Conductor Tyranno (Rush)
160213078.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 monster on your field to the GY.
[EFFECT]
Inflict 1000 damage to your opponent. This turn, this card cannot attack.

160213082.name: Lightning Vortex (Rush)
160213082.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 card from the hand to the GY.
[EFFECT]
Destroy all face-up monsters on your opponent’s field.

160213084.name: Drowning Mirror Force (Rush)
160213084.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When an opponent's monster declares a direct attack.
[EFFECT]
Shuffle all Attack Position monsters from your opponent's field into the owner's Deck.

160213169.name: Pliage the Sacred Shooting Star
160213169.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have not drawn a card during this Main Phase.
[EFFECT]
Add 1 "Star Restart" or "Star of the Beginning" from your Graveyard to your hand. Then, draw 1 card.

160214001.name: Eternity Aether Dragon
160214001.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During your Main Phase that you Normal or Special Summoned this card, pay 500 LP.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 card on your opponent's field. This turn, you cannot activate the effect of "Eternity Aether Dragon".

160214002.name: Dark Paladin (Rush)
160214002.description:
"Dark Magician" + "Buster Blader"
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[CONTINUOUS EFFECT]
This card gains ATK equal to [the total number of face-up Dragon Type monsters on the field and in both players' Graveyards] x 500. If you have cards in your hand, this card cannot be destroyed by your opponent's Spell Card effects, and your opponent cannot activate Legend Spell Cards.

160214003.name: Snake Princess of Purity
160214003.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up monster on your opponent's field loses ATK equal to [the number of face-up LIGHT Attribute monsters on your field] x 600 until the end of this turn. Then, if you have 3 face-up monsters on your field, draw 1 card.

160214004.name: Fadronir the Pure
160214004.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have not drawn a card during the Main Phase of the turn you Normal Summoned this card.
[EFFECT]
Each player draws 1 card.

160214005.name: Sevens Wonder Fusion
160214005.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Fusion Summon by shuffling monsters from your field or Graveyard into the owner's Deck as material, including "Sevens Road Magician".

160214006.name: Abysskite Party
160214006.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Each player sends cards equal to [the number of face-up Sea Serpent Type monsters on your field] from the top of their Deck to the Graveyard. Then, you can make up to 3 face-up LIGHT Attribute Sea Serpent Type monsters on your field with 800 original ATK gain 1600 ATK until the end of your opponent's next turn.

160214007.name: Over Rush Storm
160214007.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Place 2 monsters from your Graveyard on the bottom of your Deck in any order.
[EFFECT]
Place 1 Spell/Trap Card from your opponent's field on the bottom of the owner's Deck.

160214008.name: The Secret of Manifestation
160214008.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send up to 2 monsters from your hand and/or field to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Draw 1 card. Then, you can Special Summon 1 Level 5 or higher LIGHT Attribute Spellcaster Type monster from your Graveyard face-up to your field. You cannot activate monster effects for the rest of this turn, except LIGHT Attribute Spellcaster Type monsters'.

160214009.name: Jest of the Cosmos Princess
160214009.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 3 cards from your hand to the Graveyard, including 2 monsters.
[EFFECT]
Destroy up to 2 cards on your opponent's field. Then, if your opponent has 2 or more cards on their field, you can draw 2 cards.

160214010.name: Executie Riding!
160214010.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent Normal or Special Summons an Effect Monster face-up.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 monster with ATK less than or equal to that monster from your Graveyard to your field in face-up Attack Position. Then, you can make up to 2 face-up monsters on your opponent's field lose 1800 ATK until the end of this turn.

160214011.name: Sunset Rebirth
160214011.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent draws a card during their turn, or when a monster on your field is destroyed by an opponent's card effect.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 monster from your hand or Graveyard to your field in face-down Defense Position. Then, up to 3 other cards on your field cannot be destroyed by your opponent's card effects this turn.

160214018.name: Romanpick
160214018.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If your LP are lower than your opponent's, pay 500 LP.
[EFFECT]
Send the top 3 cards of your Deck to the Graveyard. If a Psychic Type monster(s) is among the cards sent, add 1 Psychic Type monster from the Graveyard to your hand.

160214019.name: Jundee of the Dark Path
160214019.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have 10 or more cards in your Deck.
[EFFECT]
Send the top 3 cards of your Deck to the Graveyard. Then, if an EARTH Attribute monster(s) is among the cards sent, you can draw 1 card. If you do, place 1 card from your hand on the bottom of your Deck.

160214020.name: Pot of Avarice (Rush)
160214020.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Shuffle 5 monsters from your Graveyard into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
Draw 2 cards.

160214021.name: Ghost Cyclone
160214021.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have no monsters on your field.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 Spell/Trap Card on your opponent's field. Then, if you have 3 or less monsters in your Graveyard, you can draw 1 card.

160214022.name: Back Beat
160214022.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Shuffle 2 monsters from your Graveyard into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
Shuffle 2 to 7 monsters with the same Type from your opponent's Graveyard into the Deck. Then, if you shuffled 4 or more monsters by this effect, you can draw 1 card.

160214023.name: Wicked Shadow Dark Lurker
160214023.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 Spell/Trap Card on your opponent's field and if you do, inflict 1000 damage to your opponent. Then, return this card to the owner's hand.

160214024.name: Traditional Tax
160214024.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent draws a card(s) during the Main Phase.
[EFFECT]
Send 2 random cards from your opponent's hand to the Graveyard.

160214025.name: Sevens Knight the Multistrike Dragon Knight
160214025.description:
"Sevens Road Magician" + "Multistrike Dragon Dragias"
[REQUIREMENT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[MULTI-CHOICE EFFECT]
● This turn, this card gains 500 ATK and can make up to 2 attacks on monsters.
● This card cannot be destroyed by card effects until the end of your opponent's next turn.

160214026.name: The Perfect Dragiastar
160214026.description:
"The Dragias" + 4 Level 7 monsters
[REQUIREMENT]
If your LP are lower than your opponent's, send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This turn, this card can attack all opponent's monsters once each.

160214027.name: Bandiva Duo the Elegy of the Wailing Winds
160214027.description:
2 Level 7 WIND Attribute Psychic Type monsters
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 other card from your hand or field to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This card gains ATK equal to [the total number of cards in your opponent's hand and field] x 300 until the end of this turn. Then, if you have a Normal Monster in your Graveyard, you can destroy 1 card on your opponent's field.

160214028.name: Dark Cavalry (Rush)
160214028.description:
"Dark Magician" + 1 Warrior Type monster with 2100 DEF
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[CONTINUOUS EFFECT]
This card gains ATK equal to [the total number of Spell/Trap Cards in both players' Graveyards] x 100. This card inflicts piercing battle damage. If you have cards in your hand, other monsters on your field cannot be destroyed by your opponent's card effects.

160214029.name: Elemental HERO Heliosphere
160214029.description:
"Elemental HERO Sparkman" + "Elemental HERO Avian" + "Elemental HERO Burstinatrix"
Must be Fusion Summoned.

[REQUIREMENT]
You have 10 or more cards in your Deck.
[EFFECT]
Draw 1 card and show it. Then, if that card is a monster, you can destroy 1 card on your opponent's field.

160214030.name: Ancient Gear Megaton Golem (Rush)
160214030.description:
3 EARTH Attribute Machine Type monsters whose original ATK equals their own original DEF
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[CONTINUOUS EFFECT]
Your opponent cannot activate Trap Cards when this card declares an attack. If this card was Fusion Summoned using 2 or more monsters whose original Levels are 8 as material, it can attack twice per turn.

160214031.name: Chimeratech Crush Dragon
160214031.description:
"Cyber Dragon" + 2 or more Machine Type monsters
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[CONTINUOUS EFFECT]
Monsters on your field cannot be destroyed by Spell Card effects. Face-up Machine Type monsters on your field gain ATK equal to [the number of monsters used as material for this card's Fusion Summon] x 100.

160214032.name: Harpie Lady 1 & 2 & 3
160214032.description:
"Harpie Lady" + "Harpie Lady" + "Harpie Lady"
You can Summon this card by Contact Fusion.

[REQUIREMENT]
None
[CONTINUOUS EFFECT]
This card's name becomes "Harpie Lady", and it can make up to 3 attacks on monsters each turn. This card cannot attack directly. Face-up Level 12 monsters on your field cannot be used as material for a Fusion Summon.

160214033.name: Executie Prouty Frontiere
160214033.description:
"Executie Prouty" + "Executie Leir"
You can Summon this card by Contact Fusion.

[REQUIREMENT]
None
[CONTINUOUS EFFECT]
Face-up non-Level 6 monsters on your opponent's field lose 600 ATK/DEF. When this card destroys a monster by battle and sends it to the Graveyard, gain 600 LP.

160214034.name: CAN - Eb:D
160214034.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Pay 100 LP.
[EFFECT]
Choose 1 Psychic Type monster in your Graveyard. This turn, this card's name becomes the same as that monster. Then, if you have no face-up Fusion Monsters on your field, you can add 1 "CAN:D" or 1 "Fusion" from your Graveyard to your hand.

160214035.name: Ember the Ultra Assistant
160214035.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have 10 or more cards in your Deck during the turn you Normal Summoned this card.
[EFFECT]
Draw 1 card. Then, if you have "Ember the Super Assistant" in your Graveyard, send the top 2 cards of your Deck to the Graveyard. Then, you can add to your hand 1 FIRE Attribute monster from among the cards sent. You cannot activate the effects of monsters whose original Level is 5 until the end of this turn.

160214036.name: Abysskite Ulti-Ange
160214036.description:
You can Tribute Summon this card in Attack Position by Tributing 1 "Abysskite Ange".
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Excavate the top 3 cards of your Deck. You can add 1 excavated "Abysskite Party" to your hand. Place the remaining cards on the bottom of the Deck in any order.

160214037.name: Deity of Seven Treasures - Bika
160214037.description:
If you have a monster with 2700 DEF or "Ship of Seven Treasures" in your Graveyard, you can Special Summon this card from your hand face-up to your field.
[REQUIREMENT]
Send the top 2 cards of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This card gains ATK equal to [the number of face-up Level 7 monsters on your field] x 400 until the end of this turn.

160214038.name: Neutron Blast (Rush)
160214038.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Choose 1 face-up "Blue-Eyes Ultimate Dragon" on your field. This turn, your opponent cannot activate Trap Cards when that monster declares an attack. This turn, that monster can make up to 3 attacks on monsters.

160214039.name: Harpie Cielo Light Skirt
160214039.description:
"Harpie Cielo" + 1 Level 4 or lower Winged Beast Type monster
You can Summon this card by Contact Fusion.

[REQUIREMENT]
During your Main Phase that you Fusion Summoned this card.
[EFFECT]
Add up to 2 "Harpie Lady Sisters" from your Graveyard to your hand.

160214040.name: Phoenix Dealer
160214040.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have 10 or more cards in your Deck, send 1 Level 7 monster from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Draw 1 card. Then, you can Special Summon 1 Level 9 Magical Knight Type monster from your Graveyard face-up to your field.

160214041.name: Black Volcano Dragon
160214041.description:
You can Tribute Summon this card in Attack Position by Tributing 1 Dragon Type monster.
[REQUIREMENT]
During the turn you Normal Summoned this card.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Dragon Type monster from your hand face-up to your field. Then, if you Special Summoned a monster by this effect whose original Level is 9, you can draw 1 card.

160214042.name: Wicked Dragon of Darkness
160214042.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During your Main Phase that you Normal or Special Summoned this card.
[EFFECT]
Send the top 2 cards of your Deck to the Graveyard. Then, you can add 1 "Dragon Knight of Darkness" or 1 Level 9 Dragon Type monster with 2500 ATK from your Graveyard to your hand.

160214043.name: Shadowbringer Dragon
160214043.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During the turn you Normal Summoned this card.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 "Nightbringer Dragon" or 1 DARK Attribute Dragon Type monster with 1100 ATK/500 DEF from your Graveyard to your field in face-up Defense Position.

160214044.name: Maginical Fantastic
160214044.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During the turn you Normal Summoned this card.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Psychic Type monster with 100 ATK or DEF from your Graveyard face-up to your field. You cannot Normal Summon Level 2 Effect Monsters until the end of this turn.

160214045.name: Jointech Baby Tyrant
160214045.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During the turn you Normal Summoned this card.
[EFFECT]
Send the top 2 cards of your Deck to the Graveyard. Then, if you have 3 or more Machine Type monsters in your Graveyard, you can add 1 "Jointech Joint" from your Graveyard to your hand.

160214046.name: Preferlyre
160214046.description:
If you have a face-up WIND Attribute Psychic Type monster on your field, you can Normal Summon this card without Tributing.
[REQUIREMENT]
Your opponent has 4 or less cards in their hand during the turn you Normal Summoned this card.
[EFFECT]
Your opponent draws 3 cards. Then, increase this card's Level by 2 until the end of this turn. Then, you can add 1 "Fusion" or "Psyquip Fusion" from your Graveyard to your hand.

160214047.name: Sitarloot
160214047.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have a face-up Level 7 or higher WIND Attribute Psychic Type monster on your field during the turn you Normal Summoned this card, send 1 card from your field to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Return 1 Spell/Trap Card from your opponent's field to the owner's hand. Then, you can add 1 Equip Spell Card from your Graveyard to your hand.

160214048.name: Ancient Gear Hunting Hound (Rush)
160214048.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Your opponent has a monster on their field and you have another face-up EARTH Attribute Machine Type monster on your field during the turn you Normal Summoned this card.
[EFFECT]
Inflict 600 damage to your opponent. Then, you can Fusion Summon an EARTH Attribute Machine Type monster whose ATK equals its own DEF by sending Effect Monsters from your hand and/or field to the Graveyard as material.

160214049.name: Cyber Basilisk
160214049.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have a face-up Level 5 or higher Machine Type monster on your field.
[EFFECT]
Choose 1 face-up monster on your opponent's field, and change it to face-down Defense Position. Then, if you have a face-up Level 8 or higher Machine Type Fusion Monster on your field, you can destroy the chosen monster.

160214050.name: Executie Mates
160214050.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Reveal 1 Level 6 monster with 500 DEF in your hand.
[EFFECT]
Increase this card's Level by 2 until the end of this turn. Then, if you have not drawn a card during this Main Phase, you can draw 1 card. This turn, you cannot attack with Level 7 or higher monsters.

160214051.name: The Versus Fusion
160214051.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Fusion Summon a monster that lists "The Dragias" as material by shuffling 1 or more Normal Monsters from your field and 1 or more monsters from your Graveyard into the owner's Deck as material. Dragon Type monsters cannot be used as material by this effect, except "The Dragias".

160214052.name: Harpie's Feather Duster (Rush)
160214052.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Destroy all Spell/Trap Cards on your opponent's field.

160214501.name: Eternity Aether Dragon
160214501.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During your Main Phase that you Normal or Special Summoned this card, pay 500 LP.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 card on your opponent's field. This turn, you cannot activate the effect of "Eternity Aether Dragon".

160215002.name: Zera the Evil Fiend
160215002.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have a Normal Monster with 1600 ATK in your Graveyard during your Main Phase that you Ritual Summoned this card.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Fiend Type non-Effect Monster from your Graveyard face-up to your field.

160215003.name: Warrior of Zera (Rush)
160215003.description: A wandering warrior who seeks the sanctuary where he can gain the power of the Archlords. To escape the temptation of evil fiends, he fights solo day by day.

160215004.name: Ryu-Kishin Powered (Rush)
160215004.description: A gargoyle enhanced by the powers of darkness. Very sharp talons make it a worthy opponent.

160215005.name: Wanderer of Zera
160215005.description:
You can Tribute Summon this card in Attack Position by Tributing 1 Normal Monster with 1600 original ATK.
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Set 1 "Zera Ritual" from your Graveyard to your Spell & Trap Zone.

160215006.name: Ominous Ogre of Yamimakai
160215006.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During your Main Phase that you Normal or Special Summoned this card.
[EFFECT]
Send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard. Then, you can Special Summon 1 "Wanderer of Zera" from your Graveyard to your field in face-up Defense Position.

160215007.name: Wicked Dragon with the Ominous Head
160215007.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Send the top 2 cards of your Deck to the Graveyard. Then, you can add 1 "Ominous Ogre of Yamimakai" or 1 "The Sword of Zera" from your Graveyard to your hand.

160215008.name: Zera Ritual (Rush)
160215008.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Ritual Summon "Zera the Mant" by sending monsters from your hand and/or field to the Graveyard whose total Levels equal 8 or more as material (you cannot use more monsters than necessary as material).

160215009.name: Zera Advent
160215009.description:
This card's name becomes "Zera Ritual" while in the Graveyard.
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Ritual Summon "Zera the Mant" or "Zera the Evil Fiend" by sending face-up monsters from your field to the Graveyard whose total Levels equal 8 or more as material (you cannot use more monsters than necessary as material).

160215010.name: The Sword of Zera
160215010.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Equip to a face-up "Warrior of Zera" or "Zera the Mant" on your field.
[EFFECT]
During your turn, the equipped monster gains 1000 ATK and inflicts piercing battle damage (if the ATK of the attacking monster exceeds the DEF of the attack target, inflict the difference).

160215011.name: Zera's Research
160215011.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Send the top 2 cards of your Deck to the Graveyard. Then, you can add 1 Level 4 EARTH or DARK Attribute Normal Monster with 1600 ATK or 1 "Zera Ritual" from your Graveyard to your hand.

160215012.name: Jagged Claw Attack
160215012.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have "Zera the Mant" face-up on your field.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 card on your opponent's field.

160215013.name: Wicked Fire Blast of Zera
160215013.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent Normal or Special Summons a monster while you have "Zera the Mant" face-up on your field.
[EFFECT]
