Destroy 1 card on your opponent's field. Then, you can inflict 1000 damage to your opponent.

160215014.name: Ever-Grace Princess Mai
160215014.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During your Main Phase that you Special Summoned this card, send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This card cannot be destroyed by your opponent's card effects until the end of their next turn. Then, if you have "Grace Princess Kana" in your Graveyard, you can destroy 1 monster on your opponent's field. If you do, this card cannot attack directly this turn.

160215015.name: Ever-Grace Princess Mari
160215015.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During your Main Phase that you Special Summoned this card, send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This card gains 700 ATK until the end of this turn. Then, if you have "Grace Princess Kana" in your Graveyard, this card can make up to 2 attacks on monsters this turn.

160215016.name: Grace Princess Mai
160215016.description: The eldest Grace Princess sister. She adores Kana.

160215018.name: Grace Princess Kaori
160215018.description:
You can Special Summon this card from your hand face-up to your field by revealing 1 LIGHT Attribute Aqua Type Normal Monster with 1400 DEF in your hand.
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Gain 500 LP. Then, you can add 1 "Grace Princess Kana" or 1 "Grace Hakama Fitting Ceremony" from your Graveyard to your hand.

160215019.name: Grace Princess Mari
160215019.description:
You can Special Summon this card from your hand face-up to your field by revealing 1 LIGHT Attribute Aqua Type Normal Monster with 1400 DEF in your hand.
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This card gains 600 ATK until the end of this turn. Then, you can add 1 "Grace Princess Kana" or 1 "Grace Hakama Fitting Ceremony" from your Graveyard to your hand.

160215020.name: Grace Princess Hina
160215020.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Place 1 card from your hand on the bottom of the Deck.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 "Grace Princess Kana" or Level 7 LIGHT Attribute Aqua Type Normal Monster from your Graveyard to your field in face-up Defense Position. Then, if you Special Summoned "Grace Princess Kana" by this effect, you can Set 1 Ritual Spell Card from your Graveyard to your Spell & Trap Zone.

160215021.name: Grace Bird
160215021.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have 10 or more cards in your Deck, send 1 LIGHT Attribute Aqua Type monster from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Draw 1 card. Then, you can add 1 "Grace Princess Kana" from your Graveyard to your hand.

160215022.name: Grace Cat
160215022.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Change this Attack Position card to face-up Defense Position.
[EFFECT]
Excavate the top 6 cards of your Deck. You can add 1 excavated "Grace Princess Kana" to your hand. Place the remaining cards on the bottom of the Deck in any order.

160215023.name: Grace Hakama Fitting Ceremony
160215023.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Ritual Summon "Ever-Grace Princess Mai" or "Ever-Grace Princess Mari" by sending LIGHT Attribute Aqua Type monsters from your hand and/or field to the Graveyard whose total Levels equal 9 or more as material (you cannot use more monsters than necessary as material). You cannot use Effect Monsters in the hand as material by this effect.

160215024.name: Grace Happiness Diary
160215024.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have 3 or more LIGHT Attribute Aqua Type monsters in your Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Excavate the top 3 cards of your Deck. You can add 1 excavated LIGHT Attribute Aqua Type monster or 1 Ritual Spell Card to your hand. Place the remaining cards on the bottom of the Deck in any order.

160215031.name: Twin Blaze Fiend Angel Archel
160215031.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have a FIRE Attribute Maximum Monster in your Graveyard, send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This card gains ATK equal to [the number of FIRE Attribute Maximum Monsters in your Graveyard] x 300 until the end of this turn. Then, if you have 3 or more Maximum Monsters in your Graveyard, this card inflicts piercing battle damage this turn.

160215032.name: Twin Blaze Fiend Angel Lunael
160215032.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[CONTINUOUS EFFECT]
If you have another face-up Level 10 FIRE Attribute monster on your field, face-up monsters on your opponent's field lose 1000 ATK/DEF. If you have 3 or more Maximum Monsters in your Graveyard, your opponent cannot activate Trap Cards when your Level 10 FIRE Attribute monsters declare attacks.

160215033.name: Blaze Fiend Overlord Zebulth
160215033.description:
You can Special Summon this card from your hand face-up to your field by sending 2 other cards from your hand to the Graveyard.
[REQUIREMENT]
During your Main Phase that you Normal or Special Summoned this card.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Level 10 FIRE Attribute Fiend Type monster from your Graveyard to your field in face-up Defense Position, except a monster with 2400 ATK. Then, you can change the battle position of 1 face-up Ritual Monster on your field.

160215035.name: Police Hound of the Blaze Fiends
160215035.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 FIRE Attribute Fiend Type monster from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Send the top 4 card of your Deck to the Graveyard. Then, you can add to your hand 1 FIRE Attribute Fiend Type monster from among the cards sent, except a monster with 900 ATK.

160215036.name: Altar of the Twin Blaze Fiends
160215036.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Ritual Summon "Twin Blaze Fiend Angel Archel" or "Twin Blaze Fiend Angel Lunael" by sending Fiend Type monsters from your hand and/or field to the Graveyard whose total Levels equal 10 as material. Then, if you sent a monster in Maximum Mode to the Graveyard by this effect, while the monster Special Summoned by this effect is face-up, it gains 2000 ATK/DEF, and cannot be destroyed by card effects.

160215037.name: Celeb Rose Luxury Magicians
160215037.description:
"Celeb Rose Magician" + "Celeb Rose Witch"

[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Level 9 or lower LIGHT Attribute Spellcaster Type monster from your Graveyard to your field in face-up Defense Position. Then, if this card is equipped with an Equip Spell Card, this card can make up to 2 attacks on monsters this turn.

160215038.name: Celeb Rose Fabulous Magician
160215038.description:
"Celeb Rose Magician" + "Celeb Rose Witch"

[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 face-up monster on your opponent's field. Then, you can add 1 Equip Spell Card from your Graveyard to your hand.

160215039.name: Celeb Rose Incognito Magician
160215039.description:
"Celeb Rose Magician" + "Celeb Rose Witch"
You can Summon this card by Contact Fusion.

[REQUIREMENT]
During your Main Phase that you Fusion Summoned this card.
[EFFECT]
Send 1 monster from your field to the Graveyard. Then, you can make 1 face-up monster on your opponent's field lose ATK equal to [the original ATK of the monster sent to the Graveyard by this effect] until the end of this turn.

160215040.name: Celeb Rose Rich Magicians
160215040.description:
"Celeb Rose Sorcerer" + "Celeb Rose Mage"
[REQUIREMENT]
During your Main Phase that you Special Summoned this card.
[EFFECT]
Set up to 2 Equip Spell Cards, "Fusion", and/or "Celeb Revelation" from your Graveyard to your Spell & Trap Zone. Then, you can destroy 1 Spell/Trap Card on your opponent's field. You cannot activate the effects of Level 7 Fusion Monsters for the rest of this turn.

160215041.name: Celeb Rose Influencers
160215041.description:
"Celeb Rose Enchanter" + "Celeb Rose Wiz"

[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Place 1 monster from your opponent's Graveyard on the bottom of the Deck, and this card gains ATK equal to [the Level of the monster placed by this effect] x 200 until the end of this turn. Then, if this card is equipped with an Equip Spell Card, this turn, this card cannot be destroyed by card effects and can make up to 2 attacks on monsters.

160215042.name: Celeb Rose Gossip Magician
160215042.description:
"Celeb Rose Magician" + "Darkness Paparazzi"

[REQUIREMENT]
None
[CONTINUOUS EFFECT]
This card gains ATK equal to [the number of Equip Spell Cards in your Graveyard] x 400. If you have a face-up Spell Card on your field, this card cannot be destroyed by battle.

160215043.name: Celeb Rose Gossip Witch
160215043.description:
"Celeb Rose Witch" + "Darkness Paparazzi"

[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 Spell/Trap Card on your opponent's field. Then, if you have a face-up Spell Card on your field, draw 1 card.

160215044.name: Celeb Rose Magician
160215044.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 face-up Equip Spell Card from your field to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 face-up Level 8 or lower monster on your opponent's field. Then, if you have 3 or more Spell Cards in your Graveyard, this card gains 700 ATK until the end of this turn.

160215045.name: Celeb Rose Witch
160215045.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have "Celeb Rose Magician" in your Graveyard, send 1 LIGHT Attribute Spellcaster Type monster or 1 Spell Card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 "Celeb Rose Magician" or 1 Level 9 or lower Spellcaster Type Fusion Monster from your Graveyard face-up to your field.

160215046.name: Celeb Rose Warlock
160215046.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send up to 2 face-up Level 5 or lower monsters from your field to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Level 7 or higher LIGHT Attribute Spellcaster Type monster from your Graveyard face-up to your field. If you Special Summoned "Celeb Rose Magician" by this effect, you can Special Summon 1 "Celeb Rose Witch" from your Graveyard face-up to your field.

160215047.name: Celeb Rose Sorcerer
160215047.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 3 face-up LIGHT Attribute Spellcaster Type monsters from your field to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 LIGHT Attribute Spellcaster Type monster with 2500 or less ATK from your Graveyard face-up to your field. Then, you can Set 1 "Charis Magic Scepter - Death Wand" from your Graveyard in your Spell & Trap Zone.

160215048.name: Celeb Rose Enchanter
160215048.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Shuffle 2 cards from your hand into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 LIGHT Attribute Spellcaster Type monster from your Graveyard to your field in face-up Defense Position. If you Special Summoned a Level 5 or higher monster by this effect, you can add 1 "Fusion" from your Graveyard to your hand.

160215049.name: Celeb Rose Mage
160215049.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have "Celeb Rose Magician" or an Equip Spell Card in your Graveyard during the turn you Normal Summoned this card.
[EFFECT]
Add 1 "Charis Magic Scepter - Death Wand" or "Fusion" from your Graveyard to your hand.

160215050.name: Celeb Rose Wiz
160215050.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During the turn you Normal Summoned this card, reveal 1 LIGHT Attribute Spellcaster Type monster or 1 Equip Spell Card in your hand to your opponent.
[EFFECT]
Send the top 4 cards of your Deck to the Graveyard. Then, you can add 1 "Celeb Rose Magician"/"Celeb Rose Witch"/"Fusion" from among the cards sent to the Graveyard by this effect to your hand.

160215057.name: Divinebreath the Orchestral Music Fiend
160215057.description:
"Digisoon the Music Fiend" + "Boton the Music Princess"

[REQUIREMENT]
Send up to 3 cards from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This turn, this card cannot be destroyed by your opponent's Trap Card effects, and if it attacks a Defense Position monster, inflict piercing battle damage (if the ATK of the attacking monster exceeds the DEF of the attack target, inflict the difference). Also, if you activated this effect during your Main Phase this card was Special Summoned, it gains ATK equal to [the number of monsters sent to the Graveyard to meet the requirement] x 1000 until the end of this turn.

160215058.name: Full Orchestra the Music Fiend
160215058.description:
"Ensembullfighter the Music Fiend" + "Boton the Music Princess"

[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Destroy all face-down cards in your opponent's Spell & Trap Zone. Then, this card gains ATK equal to [the number of cards destroyed by this effect] x 600 until the end of this turn.

160215059.name: Axetion Melody the Music Princess
160215059.description:
"Tubardiche the Music Princess" + "Boton the Music Princess"

[REQUIREMENT]
Place 1 Spell Card from your Graveyard on either the top or bottom of the Deck.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up monster on your opponent's field loses 2000 ATK/DEF until the end of your opponent's next turn. Then, if you placed "Straight Pierce" or "Fusion" to meet the requirement, you can draw 1 card.

160215060.name: Tune Flutomahawk the Music Princess
160215060.description:
"Flutomahawk the Music Princess" + "Boton the Music Princess"
You can Summon this card by Contact Fusion (Fusion Summon it by shuffling the above face-up monsters from your field into the owner's Deck as material).

[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Send the top 4 cards of your Deck to the Graveyard. Then, you can Special Summon 1 Level 7 or higher WIND Attribute Warrior Type monster from your Graveyard face-up to your field.

160215061.name: Flutomahawk the Music Princess
160215061.description: The vanguard of the band. She creates beautiful melodies by swinging her axes through the air. Some believe she chooses her outfit to hide her weaponry, but it's just because she gets cold easily.

160215062.name: Boton the Music Princess
160215062.description: The mediator of the band. She conducts her unique and colorful group of friends with her nimble polemanship. She sulks and pouts when people point out her glasses.

160215063.name: Digisoon the Music Fiend
160215063.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If your opponent has a Defense Position monster on their field, send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This card gains ATK equal to [the number of Defense Position monsters on the opponent's field] x 800 until the end of this turn.

160215064.name: Ensembullfighter the Music Fiend
160215064.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This turn, while this card is face-up, your opponent cannot activate Trap Cards when your WIND Attribute Warrior Type monsters declare attacks.

160215065.name: Tubardiche the Music Princess
160215065.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have another face-up Warrior Type monster on your field during the turn you Normal Summoned this card.
[EFFECT]
Add 1 Level 7 or higher WIND Attribute monster and 1 Warrior Type Normal Monster from your Graveyard to your hand. This turn, you cannot activate monster effects, except WIND Attribute Warrior or Beast Type monsters'.

160215066.name: Cornetlass the Music Princess
160215066.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During the turn you Normal Summoned this card.
[EFFECT]
Excavate the top 5 cards of your Deck. You can add 1 excavated WIND Attribute Warrior Type Normal Monster or 1 "Fusion" to your hand. Place the remaining cards on the bottom of the Deck in any order. This turn, you can only attack with WIND Attribute Warrior Type monsters.

160215067.name: Trombow the Music Princess
160215067.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send the top 2 cards of your Deck, and 1 WIND Attribute Warrior Type monster from your hand, to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Draw 1 card. Then, if you have a Normal Monster in your Graveyard, you can change the battle position of 1 monster on the field.

160215071.name: Stratohammer Mjolnir
160215071.description:
If you have no monsters on your field, you can Normal Summon this card without Tributing.
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 other card on your field or the top 2 cards of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Increase the Level of 1 face-up monster on your field by 4 until the end of this turn.

160215072.name: Lichy the Hopeful
160215072.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have 10 or more cards in your Deck during the turn you Normal Summoned this card, place 1 monster from your Graveyard on the bottom of the Deck.
[EFFECT]
Send the top 3 cards of your Deck to the Graveyard. Then, if you placed a Ritual Monster to meet the requirement, you can add 1 card sent to the Graveyard by this effect to your hand.

160215084.name: Tide-Ride Bluefin
160215084.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During your Main Phase that you Ritual Summoned this card.
[EFFECT]
Send the top 2 cards of your Deck to the Graveyard. Then, if a Fish Type monster or Spell Card is among the cards sent, you can destroy 1 Spell/Trap Card on your opponent's field.

160215085.name: Bluefin Oath
160215085.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During a turn you have not Special Summoned a monster.
[EFFECT]
Ritual Summon "Tide-Ride Bluefin" by sending face-up monsters from your field to the Graveyard whose total Levels equal 4 or more as material (you cannot use more monsters than necessary as material).

160215086.name: United We Stand (Rush)
160215086.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Equip to 1 face-up monster on your field.
[EFFECT]
The equipped monster gains ATK/DEF equal to [the number of face-up monsters on your field] x 800.

160215093.name: Battletested Gaia The Fierce Knight
160215093.description:
You can Tribute Summon this card in Attack Position by Tributing 1 face-up Level 5 or higher monster.

[REQUIREMENT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This card's name becomes "Gaia The Fierce Knight" this turn. Then, you can Fusion Summon by shuffling this card from your field and 1 monster from your field or Graveyard into the owner's Deck as material.

160215094.name: Veteran Curse of Dragon
160215094.description:
If you have no monsters on your field, you can Special Summon this card from your hand face-up to your field.

[REQUIREMENT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This card's name becomes "Curse of Dragon" this turn. Then, you can Fusion Summon by shuffling this card from your field and 1 monster from your field or Graveyard into the owner's Deck as material.

160215114.name: Ever-Grace Princess Mai
160215114.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During your Main Phase that you Special Summoned this card, send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This card cannot be destroyed by your opponent's card effects until the end of their next turn. Then, if you have "Grace Princess Kana" in your Graveyard, you can destroy 1 monster on your opponent's field. If you do, this card cannot attack directly this turn.

160215115.name: Ever-Grace Princess Mari
160215115.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During your Main Phase that you Special Summoned this card, send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This card gains 700 ATK until the end of this turn. Then, if you have "Grace Princess Kana" in your Graveyard, this card can make up to 2 attacks on monsters this turn.

160215116.name: Grace Princess Mai
160215116.description: The eldest Grace Princess sister. She adores Kana.

160215124.name: Grace Happiness Diary
160215124.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have 3 or more LIGHT Attribute Aqua Type monsters in your Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Excavate the top 3 cards of your Deck. You can add 1 excavated LIGHT Attribute Aqua Type monster or 1 Ritual Spell Card to your hand. Place the remaining cards on the bottom of the Deck in any order.

160301001.name: Sevens Road Magician
160301001.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This card gains ATK equal to [the number of different Attributes in your Graveyard] x 300, until the end of this turn.

160301002.name: Torna the Windweaver
160301002.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Change the battle position of 1 monster on your opponent's field (Attack Position becomes face-up Defense Position, Defense Position becomes face-up Attack Position).

160301003.name: Ansler the Magical Swordsman
160301003.description: A magical sword that uses a flame spirit puppet to wield itself. It is said that the sword recognizes the one who can best the flame spirit as its true wielder.

160301004.name: Hydro Magician
160301004.description: A young wizard who can communicate telepathically with water. His brilliant blue dance leaves his foes in awe.

160301005.name: Dark Sorcerer
160301005.description: A sorcerer whose hands have been tainted by the forbidden arts. He does not yet know the price for the power he desired.

160301006.name: Mystic Dealer
160301006.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 Spellcaster Type monster from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Draw 1 card.

160301007.name: Magical Beast Wolfang
160301007.description: The former familiar of a well-known magician. At some point its magical power surpassed that of its master, and it now toys with its foes by manipulating flames at will.

160301008.name: Spell Archer
160301008.description: A young bowman loved by the wind. His arrows are made from magic and fly endlessly.

160301009.name: Shining Shaman
160301009.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send this face-up card from your field to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up Level 4 or lower Spellcaster Type monster on your field can attack directly this turn.

160301010.name: Straynge Cat
160301010.description: A familiar said to hold great powers. It doesn't like being alone, and is very lonely now that it's been separated from its friends.

160301011.name: Wind Spirit's Protection
160301011.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up Spellcaster Type monster on your field gains 1000 ATK until the end of the turn.

160301012.name: Magical Stream
160301012.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have a face-up Spellcaster Type monster on your field.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 Spell/Trap Card on your opponent's field.

160301013.name: Dark Revelation
160301013.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When an opponent's monster declares an attack, shuffle 4 Spellcaster Type monsters from your Graveyard into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
Destroy all Attack Position monsters on your opponent's field.

160301014.name: Curtain of Sparks
160301014.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When an opponent's monster declares an attack and you have a Spellcaster Type monster in your Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
The attacking monster loses 500 ATK until the end of this turn.

160302001.name: Multistrike Dragon Dragias
160302001.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This turn, if this card destroyed a monster by battle, it can make a second attack during that Battle Phase.

160302002.name: Gravity Press Dragon
160302002.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up monster on your opponent's field loses 700 ATK/DEF until the end of this turn.

160302003.name: Fire Guardian
160302003.description: The gatekeeper standing watch over the path to the Fire Dragon Kingdom. Those who cannot withstand its breath do not have the right to go past it.

160302004.name: Dragon Knight of Darkness
160302004.description: A dragon knight leading a dark army. His merciless attacks have unparalleled strength, and the cursed sword he wields devours the souls of his foes and makes him stronger.

160302005.name: Dragorite
160302005.description: A dragon that spawned from an underground mineral vein. It uses the energy from an unknown ore as a power source for doing battle. The ultra-hard blows it delivers are incredibly effective!

160302006.name: Twin Edge Dragon
160302006.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This card can attack twice during this turn.

160302007.name: Dragon's Sage
160302007.description: A young priestess from a bloodline of ancient dragons. She offers daily prayers for the peace of her people. It is said her clear eyes have the power to alter the fate of those reflected in them.

160302008.name: Dragon Bat
160302008.description: Even scholars argue whether this mysterious creature is a bird or a beast. When flying in swarms, they somewhat resemble dragons, so it is possible that's what they are.

160302009.name: Phoenix Dragon
160302009.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Add 1 Level 5 or higher Dragon Type monster from your Graveyard to your hand.

160302010.name: Draco the Tiny
160302010.description: A small peace-loving dragon that will affectionately approach you if fed some nuts. The ring on its necklace is rumored to hold a great secret.

160302011.name: Dragonic Pressure
160302011.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 3 Dragon Type monsters from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Destroy all monsters on the field. If you destroyed a monster by this effect, you can Special Summon 1 Level 4 or lower Dragon Type monster from your Graveyard to your field in face-up Defense Position.

160302012.name: Dragon's Inferno
160302012.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have a face-up Dragon Type monster on your field.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 Spell/Trap Card on your opponent's field.

160302013.name: Dragon Encounter
160302013.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent Normal or Special Summons a monster.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Dragon Type monster from your hand face-up to your field.

160302014.name: Vengeful Dragon's Counterattack
160302014.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When a Dragon Type monster on your field is destroyed by an opponent's attack, send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 monster on your opponent's field.

160303009.name: Accel Wonder Splat
160303009.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Increase the Level of 1 face-up Spellcaster Type monster on your field by 2 and its ATK by 200 until the end of this turn.

160303010.name: Accel Wonder Flare
160303010.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Shuffle 1 monster from your Graveyard into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
Inflict 400 damage to your opponent. Then, if you inflicted damage to your opponent by this effect, you can make 1 face-up monster on your field become Spellcaster Type until the end of this turn.

160303013.name: Aqua Sorcerer
160303013.description: A magician with a pure mind that's beyond reproach. His unclouded eyes were supposed to always see the way to the path of reason, but at some point he began hiding them behind a mask.

160303019.name: Amazing Dealer
160303019.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have 3 or less monsters in your Graveyard, pay 300 LP.
[EFFECT]
Send 3 cards from your hand to the Graveyard, then draw 3 cards.

160303032.name: Mystery Handcuffs
160303032.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent Normal Summons a monster.
[EFFECT]
This turn, your opponent cannot Tribute 1 face-up monster on their field for a Tribute Summon while that monster is face-up.

160304003.name: Sportsdragon Closer
160304003.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If your opponent has a Level 9 or lower Attack Position monster on their field, pay 3000 LP.
[EFFECT]
This card gains 2000 ATK until the end of this turn. If your opponent has 8 or more monsters in their Graveyard, this card cannot be destroyed by the effects of your opponent's Trap Cards this turn.

160304012.name: Sylphidra
160304012.description: A dragon whelp of the four great Element Dragons, it commands the winds. It manipulates the atmosphere as it desires, using this power to protect the land.

160304022.name: Stop Defense (Rush)
160304022.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Change 1 Defense Position monster on your opponent's field to face-up Attack Position.

160304023.name: Sportsdragon Connection
160304023.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Level 5 or 6 Dragon Type Normal Monster from your hand or Graveyard to your field face-up. Then, if you have a face-up "Sportsdragon Keeper" on your field, you can add 1 "Sportsdragon Striker" or "Sportsdragon Defender" from your Graveyard to your hand.

160304030.name: Dragonic Disorder
160304030.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent Normal Summons a Level 7 or higher monster, send 1 Dragon Type Normal Monster from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Change that Normal Summoned monster to face-down Defense Position.

160305006.name: Matsugumi the Ruler's Squad
160305006.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During the turn you Normal Summoned this card, send 1 Warrior Type monster from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Set 1 "Ruler's Current", "Dark Ruler Battle Slash", or "Ruler's Dance" from your Graveyard to your Spell & Trap Zone.

160305015.name: Hero of the Yeast
160305015.description: Feel da strength ah dis breadknife-swingin' samurai who claims ta be from da Far East.

160305027.name: Bowing Brotherhood
160305027.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent draws for their normal draw in their Draw Phase, pay 1000 LP.
[EFFECT]
Change up to 2 Attack Position monsters on your field to face-up Defense Position. Then, if you have 3 Defense Position monsters on your field, you can shuffle up to 5 monsters from your opponent's Graveyard into the Deck.

160305030.name: Ruler's Dance
160305030.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When a Level 7 or higher Attack Position Warrior Type monster(s) on your field is destroyed by an opponent's attack or their Trap Card effect.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 "Yamiruler the Dark Delayer", "Kimeruler the Dark Raider", or "Semeruler the Dark Summoner" from your Graveyard to your field in face-up Defense Position.

160306003.name: Giftarist
160306003.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This card gains ATK equal to [the number of other face-up Psychic Type monsters on your field] x 400 until the end of this turn.

160306009.name: Peace Holder
160306009.description: A police officer who keeps the peace in the local area. She is struggling to solve certain missing persons cases.

160306012.name: Dream Drummer
160306012.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Shuffle 1 Psychic Type monster from your Graveyard into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
Shuffle 1 monster from your opponent's Graveyard into the Deck. Then, if you have a face-up Normal Monster on your field, you can gain 500 LP.

160306026.name: Psychic Trap Hole
160306026.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent Normal Summons a Level 5 or higher monster, and you have 2 or more face-up Psychic Type monsters on your field.
[EFFECT]
Destroy that Normal Summoned monster.

160307002.name: Asbolus the Star Knight
160307002.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Change 1 Level 5 or higher Attack Position Fiend Type monster on your field to face-up Defense Position.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up monster on the field gains 600 ATK until the end of this turn.

160307004.name: Followl of the Fornether
160307004.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During the turn this card was Normal Summoned.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Level 3 Fiend Type Normal Monster from your Graveyard to your field face-up.

160307009.name: Nessus the Star Knight
160307009.description: A man who carries the power of an evil star. He respects Echeclus the Star Knight as his teacher and mentor.

160307026.name: King's Right
160307026.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent draws for their normal draw in their Draw Phase.
[EFFECT]
Add 2 or 3 Fiend Type Normal Monsters with different Levels from your Graveyard to your hand.

160308004.name: Sigurstate Sol
160308004.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If your opponent has a face-up Level 5 or higher monster on their field, reveal up to 2 Cyberse Type monsters in your hand.
[EFFECT]
Inflict damage to your opponent equal to [the number of monsters revealed by the requirement of this effect] x 300.

160308005.name: Belsectacle Mani
160308005.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Shuffle 2 monsters from your Graveyard into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up monster on your opponent's field loses ATK equal to [the number of face-up Cyberse Type monsters on your field] x 300 until the end of this turn.

160308009.name: Connector Dog
160308009.description: An electronic beast that carries information throughout the Network World. After changes through the generations, its breed improved, resulting in a personality that lacks any hint of being two-faced.

160308015.name: Particle Acceleration
160308015.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have a face-up Cyberse Type monster on your field.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 Spell/Trap Card on your opponent's field.

160309010.name: Constructor Fighter Mixer
160309010.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If a face-up Field Spell Card is on the field during the turn you Normal Summoned this card.
[EFFECT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard. Then, if you sent a Wyrm Type Normal Monster to the Graveyard by this effect, you can draw 1 card.

160309011.name: Coiled Dragon of Destruction
160309011.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Shuffle the face-up Field Spell on your field into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
Inflict 600 damage to your opponent.

160309017.name: Constructor Engineer Draftannium
160309017.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During the turn you Normal Summoned this card.
[EFFECT]
Excavate the top card of your Deck. Then, place the excavated card on either the top or bottom of the Deck.

160309021.name: Barrier Armordillo
160309021.description: An unexpectedly powerful armadillo that can deflect anything that comes close. It can use its tank treads to skillfully dig.

160309027.name: Vegetation of Blisstopia
160309027.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Activate this card if you have face-up monsters on your field whose total Levels equal 10 or more.
[EFFECT]
While this card is face-up in the Field Zone, all face-up non-EARTH monsters on the field lose 300 ATK/DEF.

160310001.name: Pitch-Black Warwolf (Rush)
160310001.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[CONTINUOUS EFFECT]
Your opponent cannot activate Trap Cards during the Battle Phase.

160310002.name: Alien Shocktrooper (Rush)
160310002.description: The Aliens have used a mysterious biological substance to create a supreme race of soldiers. They do not have the natural powers of the other Aliens, but can make stunning physical attacks.

160310003.name: Dark Factory of Mass Production (Rush)
160310003.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Add 2 Normal Monsters from your Graveyard to your hand.

160310009.name: Tribute Doll (Rush)
160310009.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 monster from your field to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Level 7 monster from your hand face-up to your field. It cannot attack this turn.

160310010.name: Ancient Rules (Rush)
160310010.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Level 5 or higher Normal Monster from your hand face-up to your field.

160311002.name: Universe Dea
160311002.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up monster on your opponent's field loses 800 ATK until the end of this turn. Then, if you sent a Galaxy Type Normal Monster to the Graveyard to meet the requirement, gain 800 LP.

160311003.name: Cosmo Titan
160311003.description: An invasion weapon controlled by five rings. When it arrives, it crushes entire civilizations underfoot. Dyugyaai Bu Zuwaai!

160311004.name: Galactica Amnesia
160311004.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Place 1 card from your hand on the bottom of the Deck.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 2 Level 6 or lower Galaxy Type Normal Monsters from your Graveyard face-up to your field. This turn, you can only attack with Galaxy Type monsters.

160311005.name: Rebirth Cycle
160311005.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Shuffle 4 Galaxy Type monsters from your Graveyard into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
Draw 1 card.

160311006.name: Heaven Gancel
160311006.description: A spirit dragon entrusted with the feelings and dreams of the unsullied stars. It attacks by resonating with a pure heart. N'gorudu Guay!

160311007.name: Silver Seyfert
160311007.description: A knight that wanders across the galaxy looking for strong fighters. Kuinduragyomai Gyuindurajimai!

160311008.name: Meteorhino
160311008.description: A mysterious life-form with soft skin. In order to protect itself from space carnivores, it attaches meteorites to its body. Igyai Du Uvaai!

160311009.name: Strange Traveler
160311009.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have a face-up Galaxy Type Normal Monster on your field, send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up monster on your opponent's field loses 500 ATK until the end of this turn.

160311011.name: Bright Sentinel
160311011.description: A galactic warrior that protects order. When its companions are in trouble, it comes rushing with a flash. Migyui Gyaron Gonaidyue!

160311012.name: Shadow Sentinel
160311012.description: A galactic warrior that won't forgive evil. It pierces through the everlasting darkness with a single powerful attack. Hidyunri Va Yamedie!

160311013.name: Vortex Shooter
160311013.description: A galactic warrior that attacks by throwing saucers. Igyai Du Zuwaai!

160311014.name: Galactic Enforcer
160311014.description: A space weapon that has a similar structure to the spiral galaxy. It attacks with its tentacles that it can move at will. Wajaa!

160311015.name: Orbit Skater
160311015.description: A G-boy that freely flies around the universe. Lately, he's been mingling with grown-ups in the interplanetary streets. Izunduemo Idushower!

160311016.name: Sorapuyo
160311016.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have 10 or more monsters in your Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Draw 1 card. Then, send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.

160311017.name: Transam Kleine
160311017.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have no other monsters on your field.
[EFFECT]
Add 1 LIGHT Attribute Galaxy Type Normal Monster from your Graveyard to your hand. This turn, you can only attack with Galaxy Type monsters.

160311018.name: Interstellime
160311018.description: A slime made out of interstellar matter gas. It has a faint lime scent. Yashigyuei!

160311019.name: Asteroeva
160311019.description: A space life form that travels through space by piloting a UFO that looks like a rock. Jubidogg Higyumei!

160311022.name: Galactica Force
160311022.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Shuffle 3 Galaxy Type monsters from your Graveyard into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
All face-up Galaxy Type Normal Monsters on your field gain ATK equal to [the number of face-up Normal Monsters on the field] x 300 until the end of this turn.

160311025.name: Universal Storm
160311025.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have a face-up Galaxy Type monster on your field.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 Spell/Trap Card on your opponent's field.

160311026.name: Vacua Annihilation
160311026.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When an opponent's monster declares an attack while you have a face-up Level 7 or higher Galaxy Type Normal Monster on your field.
[EFFECT]
Destroy Attack Position monsters on your opponent's field, up to [the number of face-up Galaxy Type Normal Monsters on your field].

160311028.name: Transam Alive
160311028.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When a face-up Galaxy Type monster on your field is destroyed by an opponent's attack or their card effect and you have no other monsters on your field.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Galaxy Type Normal Monster with 1600 or more ATK from your hand or your Graveyard to your field in face-up Attack Position.

160311030.name: Nebula Power
160311030.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent Normal Summons a monster.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up Galaxy Type Normal Monster on your field gains ATK equal to [the number of monsters on your opponent's field] x 500 until the end of this turn.

160312006.name: Gadget Soldier (Rush)
160312006.description: A rust-free machine warrior born to battle.

160312008.name: Elephound
160312008.description: An elephant that can convey whereabouts using electromagnetic waves. Its tricks using its long springs are very popular.

160312010.name: Jointech Ace
160312010.description: An autonomous robot that excels at construction. Its joint parts hide an unknown power.

160312012.name: Flare Sorcerer
160312012.description: A magician with burning passion. His feelings eventually burned up his own heart.

160312018.name: Lightning Braver
160312018.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Shuffle 3 monsters from your Graveyard into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
Change 1 face-down Defense Position monster on your opponent's field to face-up Defense Position. Then, you can make all face-up monsters on your opponent's field lose 800 DEF until the end of this turn.

160312021.name: Cliptera
160312021.description: A winged dragon that glides through the room with its beautiful wings. It captures childlike minds and won't let go of them.

160312023.name: Tamabot
160312023.description: A Tamabot that just happened to be summoned. As soon as it appears, it's time for a fight!

160312028.name: Tribute Lock
160312028.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent Normal Summons a Level 5 or higher monster while your LP are lower than your opponent's.
[EFFECT]
Change that monster to face-up Defense Position.

160312030.name: Jointech Bumper
160312030.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When an opponent's monster declares a direct attack, shuffle 3 Machine Type Normal Monsters from your Graveyard into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
Destroy up to 3 Attack Position monsters on your opponent's field.

160313001.name: Vanishing Heliacal Riser
160313001.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have 2 or less cards in your hand, shuffle 1 monster from your Graveyard into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
This card gains 200 ATK until the end of this turn. Then, if a face-up Spell Card is on the field, you can draw 1 card.

160313006.name: Cosmo Aurorizer
160313006.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 Spell/Trap Card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This card gains ATK equal to [the number of Spell/Trap Cards on your opponent's field] x 500 until the end of this turn.

160313011.name: Transam Jelai
160313011.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have a face-up monster with 1600 or more ATK on your field, send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This turn, 1 face-up Level 4 LIGHT Attribute Galaxy Type monster on your field can make up to 2 attacks on monsters.

160313019.name: Galactica Jamais Vu
160313019.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have no other monsters on your field during the turn you Normal Summoned this card, shuffle 2 Spell Cards from your Graveyard into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
Draw 1 card.

160313020.name: Confeitrion
160313020.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 3 face-up Level 1 Galaxy Type monsters from your field to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 face-up Level 8 or lower monster on your opponent's field.

160313024.name: Galactica Repulsion
160313024.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have 3 face-up Galaxy Type Normal Monsters on your field.
[EFFECT]
Return 1 face-up Level 8 or lower monster from your opponent's field to the hand.

160313030.name: Galactica Lattice
160313030.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent Normal or Special Summons a monster.
[EFFECT]
Change up to 3 Attack Position Galaxy Type Normal Monsters on your field to face-up Defense Position. Then, all face-up monsters on your field gain DEF equal to [the number of face-up Galaxy Type monsters on your field] x 500 until the end of this turn.

160313032.name: Nova Spark
160313032.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent Special Summons a monster.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon up to 3 Galaxy Type Normal Monsters from your hand face-up to your field.

160314001.name: Jointech Tossceratops
160314001.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
This card is in Attack Position.
[EFFECT]
Toss a coin. If the result is heads, this turn, this card gains 1500 ATK and your opponent cannot activate Trap Cards when it declares an attack. If the result is tails, change this card to face-up Defense Position.

160314009.name: Corktrooper
160314009.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have no other monsters on your field and your opponent has 2 or less Spell/Trap Cards on their field.
[EFFECT]
Inflict damage to your opponent equal to [the number of Spell/Trap Cards on their field] x 300.

160314010.name: Tapanchula
160314010.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You Normal Summoned this card this turn and your opponent has 2 or more Spell/Trap Cards on their field.
[EFFECT]
Add 1 Level 4 Machine Type Normal Monster from your Graveyard to your hand.

160314012.name: Ground Attacker Bugroth (Rush)
160314012.description: A surface battle robot that was once used for sea warfare.

160314014.name: Carpendra
160314014.description: A mass-produced demolition machine with excellent mobility and functionality. The joints are very brittle, meaning its arms and wings often fall off.

160314018.name: Forkhawk
160314018.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have 3 face-up Machine Type monsters on your field, send this face-up card from your field to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Change 1 face-down monster on your opponent's field to face-up Attack Position.

160314020.name: Craftroll
160314020.description: A craft robot that's gained renown due to its popularity with children. It's currently featured as the mascot for an amusement park. By turning the handle on its middle, it's able to transform.

160314021.name: Stud Hedgepeg
160314021.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard. Then, if you sent a monster to the Graveyard by this effect, you can make 1 face-up monster on your opponent's field lose 500 ATK until the end of this turn.

160314022.name: Screw Armadillo
160314022.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 Machine Type monster from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Change 1 Attack Position Level 6 or lower monster on your opponent's field to face-down Defense Position.

160314030.name: Thunder Spark
160314030.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When an opponent's monster declares an attack while you have a Machine or Thunder Type monster in your Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
The attacking monster loses 500 ATK until the end of this turn.

160315001.name: Red-Boot Boost Dragon
160315001.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Choose up to 7 Dragon Type monsters in your Graveyard. Inflict damage to your opponent equal to [the number of chosen monsters] x 100, and this card gains ATK equal to [the number of chosen monsters] x 100 until the end of this turn. Then, shuffle the chosen monsters into the Deck.

160315008.name: Dual Coretls
160315008.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This card gains 400 ATK until the end of this turn. This turn, this card cannot attack directly, but it can make up to 2 attacks on monsters.

160315011.name: Beta Burn Dragon
160315011.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You Normal Summoned this card this turn and have another face-up Dragon Type monster on your field.
[EFFECT]
Inflict damage to your opponent equal to [the number of monsters on their field] x 100.

160315012.name: Applizard
160315012.description: A race of dragonoids that have transformed from being mere dragons. They demonstrate both great cunning and agility, and can wield their tablets when they attack as both swords and shields.

160315020.name: SSD Drake
160315020.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If your opponent has a monster on their field, send 1 Spell/Trap Card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 2 Level 4 or lower Dragon Type Normal Monsters from your Graveyard to your field in face-up Defense Position.

160315022.name: Dragosite
160315022.description: A rare electronic lifeform in the Network World. They don't like fighting and grow by eating Bugs.

160315024.name: Alpha Burn Drake
160315024.description: A dragon whelp with endless possibilities. It yearns for the vast and endless VR world created by goggles.

160315029.name: Dragon's Peak
160315029.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have a Dragon Type monster in your Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 face-up Field Spell Card on either side of the field. Then, you can Special Summon 1 Dragon Type monster from your hand face-up to your field.

160315032.name: RB Dragophone
160315032.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When a Dragon Type monster(s) on your field is destroyed by an opponent's attack or their card effect.
[EFFECT]
Send the top 2 cards of your Deck to the Graveyard. If you have no monsters on your field, you can Special Summon 1 "Blue-Fang Burst Dragon" or "Red-Boot Boost Dragon" from your Graveyard face-up to your field.

160316001.name: Analyze Phlogiston
160316001.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 Spell/Trap Card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Shuffle 3 Pyro Type monsters from your Graveyard into the Deck, whose total Levels equal [the total Levels of the Attack Position Level 8 or lower monsters on your opponent's field]. Then, destroy all Attack Position Level 8 or lower monsters on your opponent's field. This turn, you can only attack with 1 monster.

160316008.name: Flame Cerebrus (Rush)
160316008.description: Known to many as the "Burning Executioner", this monster is capable of burning enemies to cinders.

160316010.name: Flame Champion (Rush)
160316010.description: A warrior protected by a flaming shield that nullifies any attack.

160316013.name: Barrier Statue of the Inferno (Rush)
160316013.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[CONTINUOUS EFFECT]
Neither player can Special Summon non-FIRE Attribute monsters.

160316015.name: Doctor Red Robe
160316015.description: An expert in combustion research. The fireballs released by his gloves, which are his pride and joy, reduce everything to charcoal.

160316016.name: Flame Seeker
160316016.description: Team "Firepower Max" Sub-Leader. Recently, he's been using an ultra-high power burner that he bought using everything he owns. LET'S FIRE!

160316017.name: Methyl the Fire Genie of the Lamp
160316017.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During the turn you Normal Summoned this card.
[EFFECT]
Add 1 Level 4 Pyro Type Normal Monster from your Graveyard to your hand. This turn, you can only attack with Pyro Type monsters.

160316018.name: Ethyl the Fire Genie of the Lamp
160316018.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have no other monsters on your field.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 "Methyl the Fire Genie of the Lamp" from your Graveyard to your field in face-up Defense Position.

160316023.name: Ember the Super Assistant
160316023.description: My favorite experiment is flame color reactions! I'm gonna work hard all day today, powered by my burning spirit!

160316028.name: Scale of Flame
160316028.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Shuffle 1 Pyro Type monster from your Graveyard into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up Pyro Type monster on your field gains 500 ATK until the end of this turn. Then, you can make 1 face-up monster on your opponent's field lose 500 ATK until the end of this turn.

160316032.name: Fire Fall Blaze Barrier
160316032.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When an opponent's Level 8 or lower monster declares an attack while you have a face-up Level 7 or higher Pyro Type monster on your field.
[EFFECT]
Send the top 3 cards of your Deck to the Graveyard. Then, all face-up Level 8 or lower monsters on your opponent's field lose ATK equal to [the number of Pyro Type monsters sent to the Graveyard by this effect] x 400 until the end of this turn.

160317001.name: Voidvelg Elysium
160317001.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Change 1 face-up monster on your opponent's field to face-down Defense Position. This card gains 500 ATK until the end of this turn. Also, if you sent a monster to the Graveyard to meet the requirement, this card cannot be destroyed by your opponent's Trap Card effects this turn.

160317007.name: Voidvelg Hecatoncheir
160317007.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Change this Attack Position card to face-up Defense Position.
[EFFECT]
Inflict 500 damage to your opponent. Then, if you have a face-up Level 8 monster on your field, you can change the battle position of 1 face-up Galaxy Type monster on your field (Attack Position becomes face-up Defense Position, Defense Position becomes face-up Attack Position).

160317012.name: Voidvelg Palerider
160317012.description: Its existence is "Death" itself, bringing the souls of living to the netherworld. There is no escaping its purple-blue scythe.

160317013.name: Voidvelg Hoplites
160317013.description: The vassals of the wicked god that spring forth from the chaos of the universe. Its single, hideous eye strikes true terror into the hearts of men.

160317014.name: Dimension Others
160317014.description: A carnivorous space beast that broke its long silence and awoke from a death-like slumber. It drifts across dimensions, invading them one after another.

160317015.name: Voidvelg Globule
160317015.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Shuffle 3 DARK Attribute Galaxy Type monsters from your Graveyard into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
This turn, this face-up card can be treated as 2 Tributes for the Tribute Summon of a DARK Attribute Galaxy Type monster in Attack Position.

160317018.name: Voidvelg Meteon
160317018.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have a face-up Level 7 or higher Galaxy Type monster on your field, send this face-up card from your field to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 face-up Level 6 or lower LIGHT Attribute monster on your opponent's field. Then, inflict 300 damage to your opponent.

160317019.name: Meteorlarva
160317019.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Send cards from the top of your Deck to the Graveyard equal to [the number of face-up DARK Attribute Galaxy Type monsters on your field].

160317020.name: Voidvelg Peltast
160317020.description: A warrior with the power of the crescent moon. With its massive shield, it parries all attacks that come its way. On the night of a full moon, its hidden power awakens.

160317021.name: Void Corridor
160317021.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have a DARK Attribute Galaxy Type monster in your Graveyard, send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Add 1 DARK Attribute Galaxy Type monster from your Graveyard to your hand.

160317028.name: Void Intercept
160317028.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent Normal or Special Summons a monster face-up while the only face-up monsters on your field are DARK Attribute Galaxy Type monsters.
[EFFECT]
Send 1 random card from your opponent's hand to the Graveyard. Then, if your opponent has 2 or more cards in their hand, they can draw 1 card.

160317029.name: Void Veil
160317029.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent Normal or Special Summons a monster face-up while you have 2 or more face-up DARK Attribute Galaxy Type monsters on your field.
[EFFECT]
Change 1 face-up Level 8 or lower monster on your opponent's field to face-down Defense Position. Then, if you have a face-up Level 8 Galaxy Type monster on your field, you can return 1 Defense Position monster from your opponent's field to the hand.

160318001.name: Twin-Barrel Dragon (Rush)
160318001.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During your Main Phase that you Normal or Special Summoned this card.
[EFFECT]
Choose 1 card on your opponent's field, and toss a coin twice. If both of the results are heads, destroy that card.

160318002.name: Mirage Dragon (Rush)
160318002.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[CONTINUOUS EFFECT]
Your opponent cannot activate Trap Cards during the Battle Phase.

160318003.name: Flame Ruler (Rush)
160318003.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[CONTINUOUS EFFECT]
This face-up card can be treated as 2 Tributes for the Tribute Summon of a FIRE Attribute monster in Attack Position.

160318004.name: Archfiend Soldier (Rush)
160318004.description: An expert at battle who belongs to a crack diabolical unit. He's famous because he always gets the job done.

160318005.name: Torrential Tribute (Rush)
160318005.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When you or your opponent Normal or Special Summons a monster.
[EFFECT]
Destroy all monsters on the field.

160318006.name: Graceful Charity (Rush)
160318006.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Draw 3 cards, then send 2 cards from your hand to the Graveyard.

160319001.name: Blue-Eyes Ultimate Dragon (Rush)
160319001.description: "Blue-Eyes White Dragon" + "Blue-Eyes White Dragon" + "Blue-Eyes White Dragon"

160319003.name: Blue-Eyes Bright Dragon
160319003.description:
This card's name becomes "Blue-Eyes White Dragon" while in the hand.

[REQUIREMENT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This turn, this card's name becomes "Blue-Eyes White Dragon" and it gains 500 ATK. Then, if you have a face-up Legend Normal Monster on your field, you can destroy 1 face-up Level 8 or lower monster on your opponent's field.

160319004.name: Blue-Eyes Vision Dragon
160319004.description:
If you have a face-up Level 8 or higher Dragon Type monster on your field, you can Special Summon this card from your hand to your field in face-up Defense Position.

[REQUIREMENT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This turn, this card's name becomes "Blue-Eyes White Dragon", and if you Fusion Summon "Blue-Eyes Ultimate Dragon", this face-up card can be treated as 2 materials.

160319005.name: Absolute Lord of D.
160319005.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During your Main Phase this card was Normal or Special Summoned.
[EFFECT]
Excavate the top 4 cards of your Deck. You can add 1 excavated Level 8 LIGHT Attribute Dragon Type monster and/or 1 excavated "The Ultimate Blue-Eyed Legend" to your hand. Shuffle the remaining cards into the Deck.

160319006.name: Node of Legend
160319006.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During the turn you Normal Summoned this card.
[EFFECT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard. Then, you can add 1 "The Origin Stone of Legend" or "Sanctum of Legend" from your Graveyard to your hand.

160319007.name: Soul Drake
160319007.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During your Main Phase this card was Normal or Special Summoned, send 2 face-up Level 4 or lower Effect Monsters from your field to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Level 8 LIGHT Attribute Dragon Type monster from your Graveyard face-up to your field. This turn, your Level 7 or lower monsters cannot attack.

160319008.name: Phoenix Dragoon
160319008.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have 10 or more cards in your Deck, send 1 monster from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Gain 300 LP. Then, if you have a Level 8 monster in your Graveyard, draw 1 card.

160319014.name: Light Effigy (Rush)
160319014.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[CONTINUOUS EFFECT]
This face-up card can be treated as 2 Tributes for the Tribute Summon of a LIGHT Attribute Normal Monster in Attack Position.

160319027.name: The Ultimate Blue-Eyed Legend
160319027.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Fusion Summon a Level 10 or higher Dragon Type monster by sending up to 3 Dragon Type monsters from your hand and/or field to the Graveyard as material. This turn, the monster Special Summoned by this effect cannot be destroyed by your opponent's card effects.

160319028.name: Sanctum of Legend
160319028.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
While this card is face-up in the Field Zone, face-up Level 8 or higher Dragon Type monsters on the field gain 500 ATK, also Dragon Type Legend monsters cannot be destroyed by card effects.

160319035.name: Treasure of Eyes of Blue
160319035.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When a monster on your field is destroyed by an opponent's attack or their card effect.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Level 8 or higher LIGHT Attribute Dragon Type monster from your Graveyard face-up to your field. Then, if you have "Blue-Eyes White Dragon" face-up on your field, you can destroy 1 card on your opponent's field.

160320001.name: Elemental HERO Flame Wingman (Rush)
160320001.description:
"Elemental HERO Avian" + "Elemental HERO Burstinatrix"
Must be Fusion Summoned.

[REQUIREMENT]
None
[CONTINUOUS EFFECT]
When this card destroys a monster by battle and sends it to the Graveyard, inflict damage to your opponent equal to [that monster's original ATK].

160320002.name: Elemental HERO Burst Wingman
160320002.description:
"Elemental HERO Avian" + "Elemental HERO Burstinatrix"
Must be Fusion Summoned.

[REQUIREMENT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
1 face-up Warrior Type monster on your field gains 1000 ATK until the end of your opponent's next turn. Then, you can destroy 1 Spell/Trap Card on your opponent's field.

160320003.name: Elemental HERO Thunder Giant (Rush)
160320003.description:
"Elemental HERO Sparkman" + "Elemental HERO Clayman"
Must be Fusion Summoned.

[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 face-up monster on the field with original ATK less than this card's ATK.

160320004.name: Elemental HERO Neos (Rush)
160320004.description: A new Elemental HERO has arrived from Neo-Space! When he initiates a Contact Fusion with a Neo-Spacian his unknown powers are unleashed.

160320005.name: Elemental HERO Sparkman (Rush)
160320005.description: An Elemental HERO and a warrior of light who proficiently wields many kinds of armaments. His Static Shockwave cuts off the path of villainy.

160320006.name: Elemental HERO Clayman (Rush)
160320006.description: An Elemental HERO with a clay body built-to-last. He'll preserve his Elemental HERO colleagues at any cost.

160320007.name: Elemental HERO Burstinatrix (Rush)
160320007.description: A flame manipulator who was the first Elemental HERO woman. Her Burstfire burns away villainy.

160320008.name: Elemental HERO Avian (Rush)
160320008.description: A winged Elemental HERO who wheels through the sky and manipulates the wind. His signature move, Featherbreak, gives villainy a blow from sky-high.

160320009.name: Elemental HERO Bubbleman (Rush)
160320009.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have no other cards in your hand or field during your Main Phase that you Normal Summoned or Special Summoned this card.
[EFFECT]
Draw 2 cards.

160320011.name: Rising HERO Argent
160320011.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Reveal 1 Level 6 or 7 Warrior Type Fusion Monster in your Extra Deck to your opponent.
[EFFECT]
Excavate the top 4 cards of your Deck. You can add up to 2 excavated Normal Monsters whose names are mentioned as material on the monster revealed to meet the requirement to your hand. Place the remaining cards on the bottom of your Deck in any order.

160320012.name: Wroughtwyvern
160320012.description:
If you have a face-up Warrior Type Normal Monster on your field, you can Special Summon this card from your hand to your field in face-up Defense Position.
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Send the top 4 cards of your Deck to the Graveyard. Then, you can add 1 "Fusion" from your Graveyard to your hand.

160320013.name: Hero Boy
160320013.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have "Fusion" or "Skyscraper" in your Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Add up to 2 Warrior Type Normal Monsters and/or "Fusion" from your Graveyard to your hand. Then, send 1 monster from your field to the Graveyard.

160320014.name: Freed the Brave Wanderer (Rush)
160320014.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Place 2 LIGHT Attribute monsters from your Graveyard on the bottom of your Deck in any order.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 face-up monster on the field with higher ATK than this card.

160320030.name: Elemental Circulation
160320030.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Reveal 1 Level 6 or 7 Warrior Type Fusion Monster in your Extra Deck to your opponent and send 1 Warrior Type monster whose name is mentioned as material on that monster from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Draw 3 cards. Then, send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard. You cannot activate monster effects for the rest of this turn, except those of Warrior Type monsters.

160320031.name: Miracle Fusion (Rush)
160320031.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Fusion Summon a Warrior Type monster that cannot be Special Summoned except by Fusion Summon by placing monsters from your field and/or Graveyard on the bottom of the owner's Deck in any order as material.

160320032.name: Skyscraper (Rush)
160320032.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
While this card is face-up in the Field Zone, face-up "Elemental HERO Avian"/"Elemental HERO Burstinatrix"/"Elemental HERO Clayman"/"Elemental HERO Sparkman"/"Elemental HERO Bubbleman"/"Elemental HERO Neos"/Level 5-8 Warrior Type Fusion Monsters on the turn player's field gain 1000 ATK.

160320038.name: Quaking Mirror Force (Rush)
160320038.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When an opponent's monster declares an attack.
[EFFECT]
Change all face-up monsters on your opponent's field to face-down Defense Position.

160321001.name: Chimeratech Overdragon (Rush)
160321001.description:
"Cyber Dragon" + 1 or more Machine Type monsters
This card's original ATK/DEF become equal to [the number of monsters used as material for its Fusion Summon] x 800.

[REQUIREMENT]
None
[CONTINUOUS EFFECT]
This Fusion Summoned card can attack monsters a number of times per turn, up to [the number of monsters used as material for its Fusion Summon].

160321006.name: Cyber Dragon Rakete
160321006.description:
You can Tribute Summon this card in Attack Position by Tributing 1 LIGHT Attribute Machine Type monster.
[REQUIREMENT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This turn, this card's name becomes "Cyber Dragon". Then, you can make 1 face-up monster on your field gain 500 ATK until the end of this turn.

160321007.name: Cyber Dragon Zwei (Rush)
160321007.description:
This card's name becomes "Cyber Dragon" while in the Graveyard.
[REQUIREMENT]
Reveal 1 Spell Card in your hand.
[EFFECT]
This turn, this card's name becomes "Cyber Dragon", and gains 300 ATK.

160321008.name: Cyber Kirin (Rush)
160321008.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Send this card from your field to the Graveyard. This turn, you take no effect damage.

160321009.name: Cyber Dragon Nachster (Rush)
160321009.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During your Main Phase that you Normal or Special Summoned this card, send 1 monster from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This turn, this card's name becomes "Cyber Dragon". Then, you can Special Summon 1 Machine Type monster with 2100 ATK or DEF from your Graveyard face-up to your field.

160321028.name: Cyber Variation
160321028.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have 10 or more cards in your Deck, place 1 face-up LIGHT Attribute Machine Type monster from your field on the bottom of the owner's Deck.
[EFFECT]
Draw 2 cards. You cannot Special Summon non-Machine Type monsters until the end of this turn.

160321029.name: Cyber Rush Fusion
160321029.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have a monster on your field.
[EFFECT]
Fusion Summon a monster that lists "Cyber Dragon" as material by shuffling up to 5 LIGHT Attribute Machine Type monsters from your field and/or Graveyard into the owner's Deck as material. Then, if you have a monster on your field other than the monster Special Summoned by this effect, destroy all those monsters.

160321037.name: Cybernetic Overflow (Rush)
160321037.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent Normal Summons a monster, place 2 "Cyber Dragon" with different Levels from your Graveyard on the bottom of the Deck in any order.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 2 cards on your opponent's field.

160322001.name: Harpie Lady Sisters Triangle Beauty
160322001.description:
"Harpie Lady Sisters" + 2 WIND Attribute Winged Beast Type monsters
You can Summon this card by Contact Fusion.

[REQUIREMENT]
None
[CONTINUOUS EFFECT]
This card's name becomes "Harpie Lady Sisters", and it cannot be destroyed by your opponent's Spell/Trap Card effects. Face-up Level 12 monsters on your field cannot be used as material for a Fusion Summon.

160322002.name: Harpie Lady Feather Duster
160322002.description:
1 Level 4 "Harpie Lady" + 1 WIND Attribute Winged Beast Type Normal Monster
You can Summon this card by Contact Fusion.

[REQUIREMENT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This turn, this card's name becomes "Harpie Lady". Then, if you activated this effect during your Main Phase that you Special Summoned this card, you can destroy 1 Spell/Trap Card on your opponent's field.

160322003.name: Harpie Lady 2 & 3
160322003.description:
"Harpie Lady 2" + 1 Level 4 or lower Winged Beast Type monster
You can Summon this card by Contact Fusion.

[REQUIREMENT]
None
[CONTINUOUS EFFECT]
This card's name becomes "Harpie Lady". When you Normal or Special Summon a monster face-up, your opponent cannot activate Trap Cards.

160322004.name: Harpie Regina Splendid Armor
160322004.description:
"Harpie Regina" + 1 Level 4 or lower Winged Beast Type monster
You can Summon this card by Contact Fusion.

[REQUIREMENT]
During your Main Phase that you Special Summoned this card.
[EFFECT]
Change the battle position of 1 monster on your opponent's field. Then, if you have "Splendid Slash" in your Graveyard, you can destroy 1 Defense Position monster on your opponent's field.

160322005.name: Harpie Cara Charming Dress
160322005.description:
"Harpie Cara" + 1 Level 4 or lower Winged Beast Type monster
You can Summon this card by Contact Fusion.

[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Send the top 3 cards of your Deck to the Graveyard. Then, if you have a Level 2 Winged Beast Type monster in your Graveyard, you can make 1 face-up monster on your opponent's field lose 1500 ATK until the end of this turn.

160322006.name: Harpie Signora
160322006.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have 10 or more cards in your Deck during the turn you Normal Summoned this card.
[EFFECT]
Send the top 2 cards of your Deck to the Graveyard. Then, if "Harpie Lady" or "Harpie Lady Sisters" is among the cards sent, you can draw 1 card.

160322007.name: Harpie Belle
160322007.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During the turn you Normal Summoned this card.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Level 2 Winged Beast Type monster from your Graveyard face-up to your field. If you Special Summoned a Normal Monster by this effect, you can destroy 1 face-down card on your opponent's field.

160322035.name: Hysteric Party (Rush)
160322035.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
When your opponent draws a card(s) during their turn, or when your monster is destroyed by an opponent's attack.
[EFFECT]
Send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard. Then, you can Special Summon up to 3 "Harpie Lady", "Harpie Lady Sisters", and/or WIND Attribute Winged Beast Type Fusion Monsters from your Graveyard face-up to your field.

160323001.name: Magician of Black Chaos (Rush)
160323001.description:
This card's name becomes "Dark Magician" while in the Graveyard.
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
None

160323002.name: Ceremonial Sorcerer
160323002.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
You have a face-up Level 8 Spellcaster Type Ritual Monster on your field.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 card on your opponent's field.

160323003.name: Ceremonial Knight
160323003.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This card gains 1000 ATK until the end of this turn. Then, if you have a face-up Level 8 Spellcaster Type Ritual Monster on your field, all face-up monsters on your field gain 500 ATK until the end of this turn.

160323006.name: Winged Dragon of Chaos
160323006.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During your Main Phase that you Normal or Special Summoned this card.
[EFFECT]
Set 1 "Black Magic Ritual" from your Graveyard in your Spell & Trap Zone. Then, if you have not drawn a card during this Main Phase, you can draw 1 card.

160323007.name: Marching Beaver Warrior
160323007.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
During the turn you Normal Summoned this card.
[EFFECT]
Send the top 2 cards of your Deck to the Graveyard. Then, you can Special Summon 1 monster with 1200 ATK/1500 DEF or 1400 ATK/1200 DEF from your Graveyard to your field in face-up Defense Position.

160323008.name: Light-Calling Griffore
160323008.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Reveal 1 Warrior or Spellcaster Type Ritual Monster with 2500 or more DEF in your Extra Deck.
[EFFECT]
Set 1 Ritual Spell Card that mentions the monster revealed by this effect's requirement from your Graveyard to your Spell & Trap Zone.

160323009.name: Dark-Guiding Kuriboh
160323009.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send the top 2 cards of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Choose 1 face-up Level 8 or lower monster on your opponent's field. During your opponent's next turn, your opponent cannot attack with that monster. Then, you can Special Summon 1 "Dark-Guiding Kuriboh" or 1 Level 7 monster with 2100 DEF from your Graveyard to your field in face-down Defense Position.

160323010.name: Explorer of the Temple
160323010.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Shuffle 2 monsters from your Graveyard into the Deck.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Level 7 Ritual Monster with 2300 ATK/2500 DEF from your Graveyard face-up to your field.

160323029.name: Mind Control (Rush)
160323029.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Take control of 1 monster on your opponent's field that is not in Maximum Mode until the End Phase (when control of that monster is returned, if there is no Monster Zone to return, send it to the Graveyard). This turn, that monster cannot attack or be Tributed for a Tribute Summon.

160323030.name: Black Magic Ritual (Rush)
160323030.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Ritual Summon "Magician of Black Chaos" by sending monsters from your hand and/or field to the Graveyard whose total Levels equal 8 or more as material (you cannot use more monsters than necessary as material).

160323031.name: Ceremonial Gate
160323031.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Ritual Summon "Ceremonial Sorcerer" or "Ceremonial Knight" by sending face-up monsters from your field to the Graveyard whose total Levels equal 7 or more as material (you cannot use more monsters than necessary as material).

160401001.name: Sevens Road Witch
160401001.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Level 7 or higher, DARK Attribute, Spellcaster Type monster from your hand, face-up to your field. If you Special Summoned "Sevens Road Magician" by this effect, this card gains 400 ATK until the end of this turn.

160401002.name: Cosmic String Noodryad
160401002.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If "Outer Space" is face-up on the field, send 2 Pyro Type monsters from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Destroy all face-up Level 7 or lower monsters on the field.

160401003.name: Constructor Wyrm Buildragon
160401003.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
A face-up Field Spell Card is on the field.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Wyrm Type Normal Monster from your Graveyard face-up to your field.

160401004.name: CAN:D
160401004.description: Carrying infinite potential, she continues to chase her shining dream with a smile on her face.

160401005.name: Kimeluna the Dark Shifter
160401005.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[EFFECT]
Change the battle positions of up to 2 monsters on your opponent's field (Attack Position becomes face-up Defense Position, Defense Position becomes face-up Attack Position). Then, if you changed a battle position by this effect, you can change the battle position of 1 face-up monster on your field.

160401006.name: CAN:D LIVE
160401006.description:
"CAN:D" + "Psypickupper"

[REQUIREMENT]
Your opponent has a monster on their field.
[MULTI-CHOICE EFFECT]
● Take 2000 damage, then you can make all face-up monsters currently on your opponent's field lose 3000 ATK until the end of this turn.
● Gain 1000 LP, then you can Special Summon 1 Level 7 or higher Psychic Type monster from your Graveyard to your field face-up.

160401007.name: Sevens Road Witch
160401007.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Level 7 or higher, DARK Attribute, Spellcaster Type monster from your hand, face-up to your field. If you Special Summoned "Sevens Road Magician" by this effect, this card gains 400 ATK until the end of this turn.

160401008.name: Princess of the Flock - Miss Mutton
160401008.description: Baa-dum, baa-dum, baa-dum, baa-dum, baaaaa-dum! The sheep's in the meadow, the cow's in the corn! You can call me "miss", but I'm actually Wooly Wonderland royalty. I'm never sheepish about chowing on paper (even if it happens to be an important letter).

160401009.name: Prophecy Phrase the Colors of the Wind
160401009.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If the only face-up monsters on your field are WIND Attribute Psychic Type monsters, pay 1000 LP.
[EFFECT]
Each player with cards in their hand sends their entire hand to the Graveyard. Then, inflict damage to your opponent equal to [the number of cards sent to the Graveyard by this effect] x 200. Then, you can make all face-up monsters on your opponent's field lose ATK equal to [the damage inflicted to your opponent by this effect] until the end of this turn.

160401010.name: Cat Claw Girl
160401010.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Place 1 card from your hand on the bottom of the Deck.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 Beast Type monster with 200 DEF from your Graveyard face-up to your field. Then, if you Special Summoned a Normal Monster by this effect, you can Set 1 "Fusion" from your Graveyard in your Spell & Trap Zone.

160401011.name: Machvio of the Ultimate Aria
160401011.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
None
[CONTINUOUS EFFECT]
This card gains ATK equal to [the total number of Equip Spell Cards equipped to this card and the number of face-up Normal Monsters on your opponent's field] x 500.

160401012.name: Celeb Rose Magician
160401012.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send 1 face-up Equip Spell Card from your field to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Destroy 1 face-up Level 8 or lower monster on your opponent's field. Then, if you have 3 or more Spell Cards in your Graveyard, this card gains 700 ATK until the end of this turn.

160401013.name: Celeb Rose Witch
160401013.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
If you have "Celeb Rose Magician" in your Graveyard, send 1 LIGHT Attribute Spellcaster Type monster or 1 Spell Card from your hand to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
Special Summon 1 "Celeb Rose Magician" or 1 Level 9 or lower Spellcaster Type Fusion Monster from your Graveyard face-up to your field.

160401014.name: Elite Agent Mystery
160401014.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Shuffle 2 other face-up Reptile Type monsters from your field and 1 card from your hand into the owner's Deck.
[EFFECT]
This card gains 300 ATK until the end of this turn. Then, you can Special Summon up to 2 Level 7 or higher Reptile Type monsters from your hand and/or Graveyard face-up to your field.

160401015.name: Sevens Fear Magician
160401015.description:
[REQUIREMENT]
Send the top card of your Deck to the Graveyard.
[EFFECT]
This card's name becomes "Sevens Road Magician" this turn. Then, you can make 1 face-up monster on your opponent's field lose ATK equal to [the number of different Attributes in your Graveyard] x 300 until the end of this turn.

160401016.name: Dark Matter Enigmata
160401016.description:
